Commentary: Starts with a length ball outside off, 133.9 kph. David Warner knocks it to extra covers. The fielder has a long chase to do. They collect three runs.
Good length shaping it away from the batter, Usman Khawaja looks to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Another one shaping it away from the batter, Usman Khawaja lets it go.
Slightly shorter this time and outside off, Usman Khawaja shoulders arms at it. Three dots now.
Another dot ball as Usman Khawaja leaves this one as well.

Good length angling it into the batter, Usman Khawaja eases it to square leg for one. He gets off the mark. It looks like the new ball will be shared by Jason Holder as he is being called to bowl from the other end.
An outswinger outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Fuller and on middle, Usman Khawaja flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Good length and on off, shaping it in. David Warner defends it to short covers.
Another one angling it into the batter, David Warner fends it to short mid-wicket. Dot again.
On a length and just outside off, David Warner leaves it alone.
Just a run of the over. This one lands outside off, David Warner shoulders arms at it.
On a length and on middle, Usman Khawaja defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter one with some extra bounce, Usman Khawaja doesn't read it well and gets a hit on his wrist as the ball bounces off the deck.
Touch fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Good length shaping it away from the batter, Usman Khawaja lets it go.
On a length and down leg, Usman Khawaja looks to flick it but gets his pads as the ball rolls towards square leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Fuller and outside off, David Warner pushes it to point for a quick single.
On a length and just outside off, David Warner reads it well and makes a tight leave.
Another dot ball as David Warner lets this one go as well.
Slightly shorter one, outside off. David Warner shoulders arms at it.
Bowls a fuller one on off, David Warner defends it to short covers.
FOUR! Excellent timing. Slightly shorter one, David Warner rocks back and pulls it hard through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Good length outside off, David Warner leaves it alone towards the keeper.
FOUR! Shorter one and on off, Usman Khawaja stands tall and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary!
An outswinger and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Another length ball and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone again.
Good length and outside off, Usman Khawaja lets this one go as well.
On a length and outside off shaping it away, Usman Khawaja shoulders arms at it. Four dots now.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja defends it to short covers.
Length ball outside off stump as the batter leaves it alone here.
Slightly shorter one and on off, David Warner cuts it but finds the fielder at backward point who stops it well.
Touch fuller and outside off, David Warner shoulders arms at it.
Another one outside off as David Warner lets it sail towards the keeper.
On a length and on off, David Warner taps it to covers for one.
Back of a length and on off, Usman Khawaja pulls it to mid-wicket for a brace.
Slightly shorter one and on off, David Warner fends it to point.
Back of a length shaping it away from the batter, David Warner gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Good length and on off, David Warner eases it to mid off.
Slightly shorter and outside off, David Warner looks to pull it but misses.
A touch fuller and a quicker one as David Warner drives it straight to the man at short covers on the bounce.
A maiden from Alzarri Joseph as this one is defended towards mid off.
On a length and on off, Usman Khawaja defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja shuffles across and creams it towards deep covers for a brace.
Good length angling it in, Usman Khawaja defends this one off his front foot.
Good length and just outside off as Usman Khawaja reads it well and makes a tight leave.
Fuller one and on middle, Usman Khawaja defends it back towards the bowler.
An outswinger and outside off, Usman Khawaja shoulders arms at it.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and outside off, David Warner stands firm and cuts it through covers for a boundary!
On a length shaping it away, David Warner eases it to backward point.
FOUR! Good length and on off, David Warner knocks it with the full face of the bat through mid off for a boundary!
FOUR! Another half volley on off, David Warner stands firm and creams it through extra covers for another boundary!
Shorter one and on middle, David Warner ducks underneath it.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Alzarri Joseph finally gets his man and West Indies have a breakthrough in the game. An half volley and outside off shaping it away, David Warner falls for this delivery and looks to drive it but misses and gets a slightest of the edge. Joshua Da Silva makes no mistake and takes it well. David Warner walks out at 21.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja eases it to point for one.
Another fuller ball as this is defended towards the bowler.
Keeps bowling it fuller, Marnus Labuschagne taps it to point for one.
Slightly shorter and on the pads as Usman Khawaja flicks it towards deep square leg for a double.
Fuller one with a hint of turn, Usman Khawaja guides it to backward point for one.
Tossed up, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one and outside off shaping it away, Usman Khawaja looks to play at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length and on middle, Usman Khawaja defends it back towards the bowler.
Good length and on the pads, Usman Khawaja works it away for a single to the mid-wicket region.
Bowls it fuller and on leg, Marnus Labuschagne nudges it to mid-wicket for a brace.
On a length and outside off with some extra bounce, Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms at it.
Another one outside off as Marnus Labuschagne lets this one go as well.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja flicks it to square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! A loose delivery on middle, Usman Khawaja rocks back and pulls it through square leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja pushes it to covers for one.
Fuller again, Marnus Labuschagne nudges it to mid-wicket. The fielder does well and stops it by diving to his right. Dot.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it back towards the bowler.
Good length shaping it in, Usman Khawaja blocks it to short covers.
Back of a length in the channel angling away, Usman Khawaja lets it go to the keeper.
On a length this time, Usman Khawaja defends it to short covers. Oh, its a no ball.
Shorter one on middle, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Fuller and on middle, Usman Khawaja knocks it back towards the bowler.
On a length and outside off shaping it in, Usman Khawaja reads it well and lets it go.
Bowls it on off this time, Usman Khawaja defends it firmly towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid on and scampers through for a single.
Short of a length, Usman Khawaja makes room and carves it through covers for a single.
Fuller on the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne defends on the front foot back to the bowler.
Fuller one as this is pushed towards covers for one.
FOUR! Slightly shorter one, slower too. Usman Khawaja reads it early and pulls it hard through square leg for a boundary!
Slightly shorter one, Usman Khawaja punches it to covers for one.
Touch fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja blocks it firmly back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Overpitched and on off, Usman Khawaja stands tall and drives it through covers as the ball reaches the ropes in no time. Boundary!
FOUR! Slightly shorter this time but gets the same result. Usman Khawaja rocks back and pulls it through square leg for another boundary!
On a length and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone. Oh, its a no ball.
Another one outside off shaping it in, Usman Khawaja reads it well and makes a tight leave.
On a length and on off, Usman Khawaja defends it back towards the bowler.
Bangs a shorter one on leg, Usman Khawaja ducks underneath it. Oh, its a no ball again.
Bowls it outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Anderson Phillip begins with a back-of-a-length delivery in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne tucks this to square leg and takes a single.
Outside the off stump on a good length, Usman Khawaja raises his arms and leaves it alone.
Slightly further outside off on a good length, Usman Khawaja continues to shoulder arms to it.
Keeps bowling on a good length and angling away from outside off, Usman Khawaja is happy to leave it alone as well.
This is slightly short and outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja cuts this but with control straight to point.
Goes 'round the wicket for the last ball and serves this on a good length outside off. Usman Khawaja blocks this towards cover as the ball is angled in.
Starts off with a good length delivery in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne looks to work this leg side but gets sqaured up and in the end taps the ball down the pitch.
On a good length and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone.
Gets this close to the off pole and gets good shape away from a good length. Marnus Labuschagne judges the line of the bal well and lets it through to the keeper.
Goes slightly fuller and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne gets a solid block in towards mid off.
Bowls this slightly back of a length and angled into the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne inside edges the ball to square leg.
Maiden over for Jason Holder! This is on a good length and in line with the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne pushes this towards mid one.
Anderson Phillip continues bowling 'round the wicket to the southpaw. Goes full and just outside off. Usman Khawaja blocks this towards mid off.
Goes really full this time but angles this down leg, Usman Khawaja looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad.

FOUR! That has been crunched away! Anderson Phillip continues bowling full and outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja gets his front foot forward and caresses this to deep cover for four runs. 1000 runs for Usman Khawaja in 2022!
Bowls this short of length and outside off, Usman Khawaja pulls this in the gap to the right of mid-wicket and they take three runs comfortably.
Goes over the wicket now to Marnus Labuschagne and bowls this full, in line with the stumps. The batter blocks this back down the pitch.
Continues to attack the stumps on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne clips this to deep backward square leg for a single and will keep strike.
Goes full on a leg stump line, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this back towards the bowler.
This is full as well and just outside the odd stump, Marnus Labuschagne clips this down to long on and takes one.
Bowls this outside off on a fuller length, Usman Khawaja taps this past the point fielder and takes a single.
Full once again and pitches outside leg, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards square leg and takes one.
Fires this one full and just outside off, Usman Khawaja blocks this towards cover.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside off, Usman Khawaja goes back in the crease and looks to pull but gets a top edge into the vacant square leg region and they take a run.
Jason Holder goes full and outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja defends this solidly towards cover.
Outside the off stump and 121 clicks and on a good length. Usman Khawaja raises his arms high in the air and leaves the ball alone.
Bowls this at 126 kmph, outside the off stump and on a good length. Usman Khawaja is content with leaving this alone.
Bowls this onto the pads on a good length, Usman Khawaja clips this through the square leg region and takes a single.
Goes slightly fuller and just outside off at 122 clicks. Marnus Labuschagne is watchful as he blocks this back down the pitch.
Good movement away from a good length, just outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to this one.
Anderson Phillip starts this over from over the wicket to the left-hander. Bowls this fuller and just outside off, Usman Khawaja pushes at the ball and is beaten on the outside edge.
On a good length this time and outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja lets this go through to the keeper.
Further outside off on a good length, Usman Khawaja is not interested in playing at this one as well.
Keeps prodding at the line outside the off stump on a good length, Usman Khawaja continues to not offer a shot.
Strays onto the pads this time in a good length, Usman Khawaja clips this to deep square leg and takes a single.
Bowls this one in line with the stumps and on a good length. Some extra bounce off the surface and the ball rises sharply. Marnus Labuschagne blocks this back into the pitch awkwardly.
Jason Holder bowls this well outside the off pole on a good length. Usman Khawaja watches it go past to the keeper.
This is full and outside the off, Usman Khawaja clocks this towards cover.
Bowls this well outside off on a fuller length, Usman Khawaja shoulders his arms to this one.
Bowls this back of a length and in line with the stumps, Usman Khawaja looks to pull but misses and gets hit on his body.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja leaves this one alone.
On a good length once again and just outside off, Usman Khawaja defends this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Anderson Phillip goes full and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne strokes this to the right of point but there is a good stop from the fielder.
This is on a good length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this solidly to the off side.
Goes a touch fuller but still outside the off pole, Marnus Labuschagne strokes this firmly to the mid off fielder.
Strays down the leg side on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne looks to clip but misses and it is collected by the keeper.
On a good length this time and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets squared up and gets a thick outside edge towards the gully fielder.

Another maiden over and West Indies are building some pressure here. Anderson Phillip bowls this on a good length and just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne taps this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Jason Holder bowls from 'round the wicket and bangs this in short and quiet wide outside off. Usman Khawaja does not make a move towards the ball and leaves it alone.
Jason Holder has got his radar off as he flings this down leg side on a fuller length. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone and the keeper gets across to collect it.
This is on a good length and outside off, Usman Khawaja blocks this towards point.
Goes full and well outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja leaves this one alone.
Fuller and outside off, Usman Khawaja lets it go.
Fuller length and outside the off. Usman Khawaja shoulders his arms at it.
On a good length and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne cips this towards mid-wicket.
Gets this outside the off stump on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne looks to play at it initially but then decides to leave it alone.
On a good length once again and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne knocks this straight to the cover-point fielder.
Bowls this short and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets on top of the bounce and pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Bowls this at 146 clicks on a good length and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne raises his arms and lets it through to the keeper.
On a good length this time and just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to block and gets an outside edge towards point.
Bowls it slightly shorter and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole, Usman Khawaja continues to be patient and leaves this one alone.
Continues bowling well outside off on a good length and Usman Khawaja continues to not play a shot.
Closer this time but still outside off on a good length, Usman Khawaja blocks this to backward point.
Goes slightly fuller and outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja defends this solidly towards cover.
Angles this one in but it is wide oustide off on a good length. Usman Khawaja shoulders his arms to this one and it will be another maiden for Jason Holder.
Alzarri Joseph bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole, Marnus Labuschagne steps across the stumps and blocks the ball into the off side.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets on his toes and taps the ball towards backward point.
WIDE! Bangs this in short and outside the off pole, Marnus Labuschagne sways out of the way and lets it through to the keeper. The umpire feels its too high and calls this wide.
Bowls this a tad fuller and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne well behind the line of the ball as he taps this into teh off side.
Attacks the stumps on a fuller length, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
On a good length and just outside off, Usman Khawaja defends this firmly towards cover.
Goes full once this time and outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja strokes this straight to the cover fielder.
Roston Chase floats one full and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards deep square leg and takes a single.
Goes full and just outside off, Usman Khawaja looks to go on the back foot and is hurried into his block.
That is FIFTY for Usman Khawaja! This is slightly short and just outside off, Usman Khawaja goes deep in the crease and punches this to deep cover for a single.
This is on a leg stump line and fuller in length, Marnus Labuschagne flicks this to square leg.
Continues bowling full and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne clocks this back down the pitch.
This is straight as well and slightly short, Marnus Labuschagne goes on his back foot and clocks this towards mid-wicket. That will be DINNER on Day 1!
Good length angling it in, Usman Khawaja blocks it back towards the bowler.
Another length ball on off, Usman Khawaja defends it solidly off the front foot.
On off again, Usman Khawaja eases it to the fielder at mid on.
Bowls it outside off shaping it away, Usman Khawaja looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Similar to the last delivery, Usman Khawaja looks to block it but gets beaten again. Five dots now.
A maiden from Anderson Phillip to start with. Outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Good length angling it into the batter, Marnus Labuschagne defends it solidly towards mid on.
On a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne blocks it back towards Alzarri Joseph.
Bowls it on off again, Marnus Labuschagne taps it to the fielder at point.
Length delivery outside the off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to short extra covers.
Bowls a fuller one this time, Marnus Labuschagne nudges it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
On a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it but miscues it to backward point. Good start so far from the West Indies bowlers.
FOUR! Fuller and down leg, Usman Khawaja uses his wrists and flicks it in the gap through fine leg for a boundary!
Bowls it on off, this is defended back towards the bowler.
On a length and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
An outswinger outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone again.
Touch fuller and just outside off, Usman Khawaja slaps it but finds the fielder at point.
On a length and on off, Usman Khawaja defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne fends it back towards the bowler.
Good length angling it in, Marnus Labuschagne eases it to mid off. Dot.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards the fielder at mid on.
Slightly shorter one, angling it in. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block it but gets an inside edge as the ball hits his ribs and bounces off the deck.
Outside off this time, Marnus Labuschagne eases it to mid off.
Bowls it on off shaping it in, Marnus Labuschagne guides it to mid on and scampers through for a single.
Bowls it outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Fuller one this time, Marnus Labuschagne drives it but finds the fielder at extra covers.
A yorker and on off, Marnus Labuschagne digs it to mid off.
Slightly shorter one this time, Marnus Labuschagne taps it towards the fielder at point.
A low full toss, down leg. Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick it but misses.
Nearly chops onto the stumps. On a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to block it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball rolls towards fine leg. They collect two. Close!
Slightly shorter one outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Another dot ball as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bangs a bouncer on off, Usman Khawaja ducks underneath it.
Good length shaping it away from the batter, Usman Khawaja lets it go towards the keeper.
On a length and outside off, 135.7 kph. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
A maiden from Alzarri Joseph. Slightly shorter one and just outside off, Usman Khawaja shoulders arms at it.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne gets on his knee and drives it through covers for a boundary!
Good length angling it in, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
On a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne cuts it but finds the fielder at point who stops well by diving to his left. Dot.
Fuller one this time, Marnus Labuschagne eases it back towards the bowler.
A yorker right into the blockhole, Marnus Labuschagne digs it to point. Dot.
Good length shaping it in, Marnus Labuschagne blocks it to mid on. Devon Thomas comes into the attack now.
Devon Thomas starts off from 'round the wicket and serves this on a good length outside off. Usman Khawaja clocks this to cover.
FOUR! This has been timed beautifully! Devon Thomas bowls this a touch fuller and outside off, Usman Khawaja gets his front foot forward and carves this to deep cover for four runs.
FOUR! Two boundaries in a row now! Devon Thomas bangs this in short outside the off stump, Usman Khawaja gets on top of the bounce and pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for four more runs,
Goes over the wicket now and bowls this on a good length, outside off. Usman Khawaja blocks this solidly to covers.
On a good length once again and angling away from the left-hander. Usman Khawaja leaves this one alone.
Continues bowling outside off on a good length, Usman Khawaja shoulders his arms to this one as well.
FOUR! Australia scoring at a brisk rate now! Anderson Phillip bowls this on a good length and outside off stump, Marnus Labuschagne thumps this to deep point and collects four runs.
Goes slightly fuller and outside the off pole, Marnus Labuschagne pushes this through covers and takes a single.
On a good length this time and angling way from the left-hander outside off, Usman Khawaja blocks this towards mid off.
Goes full this time and closer to the stumps, Usman Khawaja digs this out to the mid off fielder.
Back to bowling on a good length and offers width outside off, Usman Khawaja is happy to leave this one alone.
Continues bowling on a good length, outside off. Usman Khawaja gets his front foot forward and leaves the ball well.
Devon Thomas bowls the way outside the off pole on a fuller length. There is movement for him off the wicket but Marnus Labuschagne does not need to play at this.

NO BALL! Devon Thomas bowls this on a good length and closer to the stumps this time. Good carry to the keeper as Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone. The bowler has over-stepped though and it will be a no ball.
In line with the stumps this time on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne tucks this to deep backward square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Goes really full this time and just outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne digs this out towards mid on.
Bowls this wide outside off on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne is watchful as he leaves this one alone.
Gets this closer to the batter on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne gets squared up but manages to block this towards cover-point.
Delivers this one full and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne knocks this to deep cover-point and takes a single to retain strike. Jason Holder is back in the attack here.
Jason Holder bowls this on a good length and just outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this with a straight bat towards mid on.
On a good length and outside the off pole, Marnus Labuschagne raises his arms in the air and lets the ball through to the keeper.
Bowls this slightly short and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne pulls this towards deep square leg and takes a single.

Goes 'round the wicket and serves this full, angled into the stumps. Usman Khawaja taos it to the leg side. Marnus Labuschagne looks for a single but is sent back. This would have been tight had there been a direct hit at the non-striker's end.
On a good length this time and outside off, Usman Khawaja defends this towards mid off.
Goes back to bowling over the wicket and on a good length, outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves this one alone and the keeper collects it.
Bowls this really full outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne digs this out back towards the bowler.
On a good length and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne taps this into the leg side.
Devon Thomas serves this really wide outside the off stump on a fuller length. Marnus Labuschagne decides to not play a shot.
On a good length this time and angled into the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne clips this to the right of mid-wicket and takes a single.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole, Usman Khawaja lets this go through to the keeper.
Goes full and closer to the off stump, Usman Khawaja mistimes his drive to the cover fielder.

FOUR! Poor delivery from Jason Holder and gets the treatment it deserves! Strays way down leg side on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne helps it along it way and flicks it down to fine leg for four runs. Long boundary there but the ball races across the turf.
On a good length and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne pushes this towards mid on.
Bowls this one outside the off stump on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne raises his arms and is happy to leave this one alone.

FOUR! That is a good-looking shot from Marnus Labuschagne! Jason Holder goes really full and just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne punches this down to long on and collects four runs. This is getting dangerous for West Indies as Australia are accumulating runs freely.
On a good length this time and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets a good stride forward and smothers the ball into the pitch.
Bowls this one in line with the stumps and on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards square leg tro end the over with a dot ball.

OUT! LBW! Devon Thomas has the breakthrough and it is the big wicket of the man in form Usman Khawaja! Starts the over from 'round the wicket and angles this into the stumps from outside off. Usman Khawaja looks to clip this leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal from the West Indies and the umpire raises his finger. The batter reviews straight away and the ball seems to be quite far from the bat. Ball Tracking shows the ball just clipping the leg stump and it will be the umpire's call. A much-needed wicket for West Indies and Australia have lost both their openers.
Howout: lbw b Devon Thomas

Commentary: Fuller on the stumps, Steven Smith pushes to the short cover fielder.
Back of a length angling away outside off, Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Good length and outside leg, Steven Smith lets this one go as well.
Bowls it on off, Steven Smith drives but finds the fielder at covers.
Wide! Bangs a shorter one on leg, Steven Smith leaves it alone.
On a length and on leg, Steven Smith defends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one on leg, Marnus Labuschagne pulls it but doesn't connect well. The ball carries towards square leg and lands safely. They collect one.
Good length angling it in, Steven Smith defends it to mid off.
Slower one outside off, Steven Smith lets it go.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! The skipper departs for a duck and West Indies have worked their way into the match. On a length and on off, Steven Smith looks to play it with soft hands but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and lobs towards Jason Holder who pouches it comfortably and makes no mistake. Australia are three down for 131 now!
Howout: c & b Jason Holder

Commentary: Travis Head is away. Fuller and on off, Travis Head guides it to covers for one.
On a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it solidly.
On a length and on off angling it in, Travis Head eases it to mid on.
Fuller one this time, Travis Head knocks it through covers for a brace.
Good length and outside off, Travis Head shoulders arms at it.
On a length and on off, Travis Head defends it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head guides it to point. A misfield allows the batters to steal one run.
Shorter one on off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Jason Holder bowls this back of a length and outside off, Travis Head looks to cut but does not get any timing. Miscues this towards the cover fielder.

Edged and just short! That was close! Jason Holder bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Travis Head pushes at the ball and gets a thick edge that falls just short of the second slip. The ball bounces awkwardly past the fielder and they take two runs.
This is on a good length as well and outside off, Travis Head chooses to leave this one alone.
Bowls this in line with the stumps on a good length, Travis Head blocks this with a straight bat to the left of the bowler.
Slightly short and just outside off, Travis Head rocks back and makes room to cut this to deep point for a single.
Another short ball delivered outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne gets on top of the bounce and steers the ball towards deep square leg for a single.
Alzarri Joseph bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne raises his bat and goes on his toes to leave this alone.

FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne gets a hold of this one and dismisses it out of his presence! Alzarri Joseph bowls this short and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne pulls this front of square on the leg side and collects four runs.
This is on a good length and just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this towards short mid on.

Gets this one to nip back in from a good length and in line with the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne looks to tuck this leg side but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad. There is a massive appeal from the bowler but this is clearly way too high.
Goes fuller this time and angles it into the stumps from outside off, Marnus Labuschagne clips the ball left of mid-wicket.
On a good length and outside the off pole, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this solidly towards cover.
Jason Holder bowls this on a good length and angles away from the left-hander outside off. Travis Head rocks back and punches the ball towards cover.
Goes 'round the wicket and serves this on a good length, outside off. Travis Head does not offer any shot this time.
Goes full this time and outside the off stump, Travis Head strokes this to the left of extra cover and takes a single.
Fuller in length and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne clips this into the square leg region and takes a run.
On a good length once again and angled in from outside the off stump. Travis Head is well behind the line of the ball as he blocks this towards cover.
Goes a touch fuller this time and outside the off pole, Travis Head gets low and watches it closely as it goes through to the keeper.
Roston Chase fires this one full and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone.
Flights this one and serves this full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne strokes this to the left of mid off and takes one.
Goes 'round the wicket and floats this one full, outside off. Travis Head knocks this firmly towards cover.
Full and angled into the pads, Travis Head clips this towards mid on.
Another full delivery served in line with the stumps. Travis Head kncoks this down to long on for a single.
Loopy delivery bowled full and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne lofts this over point and takes a run.
Slightly shorter one angling it in, Marnus Labuschagne fends it to square leg for one. Fifty up for Marnus Labuschagne! He has just been a run machine for Australia.
Bowls it on off, Head defends it solidly.
On a length and on off, Travis Head looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On a length and outside off, Travis Head slaps it towards deep point for one.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Good length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne knocks it to mid on and calls for one but Travis Head sends him back.
Tossed up, on off. Travis Head shuffles across and taps it to covers for one.
Another one outside off with a hint of turn, Marnus Labuschagne doesn't connect this well as the ball bounces off the deck.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne plays it to the fielder at covers.
Fuller again, Marnus Labuschagne taps it to covers for one.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller nd on off, Travis Head opens the face of the bat and drives it through covers for a boundary!
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head eases it to mid on for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Travis Head eases it to covers for one.
Slower one on off, Marnus Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket for one again.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Travis Head knocks it to mid off for one more.
Another single as this is played towards mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head punches it but finds the fielder at short covers.
Outside off this time, Travis Head cuts it but the fielder does well to stop it at point. Dot.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne taps it to covers.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket for a brace.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one.
Tosses it fuller and on the middle. Travis Head lunges forward and pushes it to mid-on for one.
Slightly shorter one down leg, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to deep square leg. They collect three runs.
Fuller one and on off, Travis Head defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne eases it t mid on for one.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Travis Head creams it through extra covers for a boundary!
Fuller again, Travis Head drives it but finds the fielder at covers. They collect one.
Another single as this is played towards deep covers.
Fuller and outside off, Travis Head knocks it to mid off. Dot.
Tossed up, on off. Travis Head knocks it but finds the fielder at mid off again.
Fuller one, on off. Marnus Labuschagne taps it to mid on.
Goes fuller, on off. Marnus Labuschagne works it to square leg for a brace. Good running!
Another fuller delivery, Marnus Labuschagne guides it to mid on for one.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head punches it to extra covers for one.
Touch fuller, on off. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it but finds the fielder at square leg.
FOUR! Well connected. Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne drives it through extra covers for a boundary. Fifty partnership comes up between Marnus Labuschagne and Travis Head now!
FOUR! Fuller again, on off. Travis Head drives it through extra covers for a boundary!
On off, this is defended out solidly.
Bowls it outside off, Travis Head eases it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne cuts it but finds the fielder at backward point.
Fuller one this time, Marnus Labuschagne knocks it to long on for one.
Bowls it on middle, Travis Head covers his line and defends it away. Thet will be TEA BREAK on Day 1.
Alzarri Joseph starts off with a full delivery outside off, Marnus Labuschagne knocks this towards cover.
Angles this into the pads on a fuller length, Marnus Labuschagne clips this to the right of mid-wicket.
Bowls this slightly fuller and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne gets squared up and gets an outside edge towards point.
Goes full and angles this into the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards the square leg fielder.
This is on the pads and on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne clips this to deep backward square leg and takes a single.
'Round the wicket to the left-hander. Alzarri Joseph angles this into the stumps on a fuller length, Travis Head flicks this to the left of mid on.
Anderson Phillip bowls this back of a length and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne gets tempted to slash at it and gets beaten all ends up.
This is slightly short as well and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets on his toes and cuts this straight to point.
WIDE! This is bowled really wide outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves this alone and the umpire call this wide.
On a good length this time and closer to the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to this one.
Continues bowling on a good length and just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this solidly towards mid on.
Bowls this wider outside off and on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone.
Keeps bowling on the outside off stump channel. Marnus Labuschagne continues to be watchful as he lets the ball through to the keeper.
Alzarri Joseph bowls this back of a length and in line with the stumps Travis Head clips this to square leg and takes a quick single.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes on the back foot and blocks th ball back down the pitch.
Goes a touch fuller and just outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne pushes this towards mid on.
Continues bowling outside off on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this solidly to the mid off fielder.

FOUR! That is a clever shot from Marnus Labuschagne! This is bowled on a length and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne waits on the ball and guides it in the gap towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Angles this into the stumps on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne clips this to deep backward square leg for one and will retain strike.
Anderson Phillip bowls this back of a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes on the back foot and punches this towards point.
Goes full this time and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne strokes this to the left of mid off and takes a single.

FOUR! What a cracking shot and it sounded lovely off the bat! Anderson Phillip goes full and offers width. Travis Head gets his front foot forward and thumps this on the up past the two fielders in the circle for four runs to deep cover
Good comeback from the bowler. Bowls this on a good length and outside off, and gets the ball to shape away from the bat. Travis Head feels for the ball but is beaten.
This is full and angled in from outside off, Travis Head mishits his punch towards mid on.

Under edge but does not carry to the keeper! Bowls this on fuller and outside off, Travis Head swings hard at this and gets a slight edge but the ball lands in front of the keeper. He is unable to collect cleanly and they take two runs.
Jason Holder bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards square leg.
On a good length once again and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne lets this go through to the keeper.
Bowls this one really full and into the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne clips this straight to the mid on fielder.
On a good length this time and just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne tucks this into the leg side.
Five dot balls now in the over. Bowls this one in line with the stumps on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne flicks this to mid-wicket.
Jason Holder continues to be tight and bowls a maiden over. This is slightly bakc of a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets on his toes and taps the ball towards mid-wicket.
Anderson Phillip bowls this back of a length and outside the off stump, Travis Head dabs this towards backward point and takes a single.
On a good length this time and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards square leg and takes one.
Bowls back of a length once again and outside the off pole, Travis Head is happy to leave this one alone.
Goes back to bowling on a good length and angles this one in from outside off. Travis Head punches this towards cover.
This one is bowled short and wide outside off, Travis Head cuts this behind sqaure on the off side but Shamarh Brooks makes a good stop to his right from point.
Bowls this fuller and just outside the off stump, Travis Head judges the line well and leaves this one alone.
On a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne taps it to covers. Dot.
Shorter one on middle, Marnus Labuschagne pulls it to mid-wicket for one.
Slower one, around off. Travis Head eases it to the fielder at covers.
Outside off this time, Travis Head slaps it to point for one.
Good length with some extra bounce, just outside off. Marnus Labuschagne makes a tight leave.
Good length angling it into the batter, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Bowls it on off, Travis Head eases it to covers.
Goes fuller this time, Travis Head knocks it bt finds the fielder at mid on.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Travis Head fends it to point.
Fuller one on off, Travis Head looks to drive it but doesn't connect well. It rolls towards the fielder at short covers.
Outside off again, Travis Head guides it to point. The fielder makes a good stop diving to his right. They collect one.
Slihtly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne works it to square leg for one more.
Short of a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne taps it but finds the fielder at backward point.
This one lands fuller, Marnus Labuschagne gently flicks it to square leg for one.
Good length and just outside off, Travis Head eases it to covers for one.
Good length angling it into the batter, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid off.
Shorter one down leg, Marnus Labuschagne looks to pull it but misses.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne pulls it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller one this time, Marnus Labuschagne knocks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
FOUR! Shorter one on off, Marnus Labuschagne uses the pace of the ball and guides it over backward point for a boundary!
On a length shaping it in, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Wide! Bowls it short and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
Good length with some extra bounce, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to play at it but misses. Close!
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne steers it to point for one.
On a length and just outside off, Travis Head looks to cut it but misses.
Good length and down leg, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one.
Bowls it on a length again, Travis Head works it to deep square leg for a brace.
Slower one and outside off, Travis Head lets it go.
Length ball, on off. Travis Head taps it to covers for a single.
Length ball and outside off stump as Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne eases it towards the fielder at gully.
Length ball angling it in, Travis Head defends it solidly.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Fuller and on off, Travis Head drives it past covers for a boundary!
Fifty up for Travis Head. His 10th fifty in the tests. fuller and on middle, Travis Head flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Good length and outside off, Travis Head eases it to covers for one.
Touch fuller one, Marnus Labuschagne covers his line and defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, this is defended towards covers.
Anderson Phillip bowls this from 'round the wicket on a fuller length and angled into the stumps. Travis Head pushes at it and gets an inside edge onto his pads.
This is back of a length and just outside off, Travis Head tucks this towards square leg and it will be another dot.
Bowls this one back of a length as well and outside the off stump, Travis Head punches this towards deep cover at they take two runs. Brings up the 100-run partnership between these two.
On a good length and angled into the stumps, Travis Head blocks this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Bowls this one full and into the pads, Travis Head flicks this to deep backward square leg and takes a single.
Bowls this one just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards mid on to end the over with a dot.
NO BALL! Devon Thomas starts off with a short ball wide outside off, Travis Head cuts this hard towards deep point for a single. The bowler has over-stepped and it wil be called a no ball.

FOUR! In the air and at the catchable height but wide of the fielder! Devon Thomas goes full and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes for the expansive drive and is early into the shot. Hits it hard enough though to make the ball go towards deep cover-point for four runs.
Bowls a full toss just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne punches this down to mid on.
Goes full and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne knocks this hard to short cover.
Bangs this in short and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes to pull this to the leg side and top edges this into the vacant deep mid-wicket region. They take a couple of runs.
This is on a good length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this to the off side.
Bowls this in line with the stumps on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne defends this back towards the bowler.
Angles this into the pads on a good length from 'round the wicket. Travis Head clips this towards deep square leg for a single.

Goes really full and angling down leg, Marnus Labuschagne gets across the stumps and looks to flick this leg side but misses. The ball goes off the pads to backward square leg and they take a leg bye.
This is on a good length and outside off, Travis Head blocks this solidly towards cover.
FOUR! What a cracking shot and Travis Head is scoring at a quick pace here! Anderson Phillip bowls this one quite full and outside off, Travis Head punches this wide off and gets a lovely boundary.
This is angled into the pads on a fuller length, Travis Head clips this towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this back of a length and outside off, Travis Head punches this off his back foot towards deep cover-point and takes a single.
NO BALL! Devon Thomas bowls a high full toss outside off as the ball slips out of his hand. Travis Head knocks this towards point and the umpire calls this no ball. He has also over-stepped!
This is on a fuller length and outside the off stump, Travis Head is watchful as he leaves this one alone.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off, Travis Head looks to cut this square but is beaten.
Bowls another full toss wide outside off, Travis Head strokes this wide of mid off and takes a single.
A low full toss bowled at 126 clicks outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne knocks this towards mid on.
On a good length and outside the off pole, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this towards cover.
This is angled into the stumps on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne clips this to the right of mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs. He is now one hit away from his century.
Roston Chase floats this down leg on a fuller length, Travis Head misses his clip and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards short fine leg.
Low full toss outside off, Travis Head knocks this to the right of mid on and takes a quick single.
Bowls this short and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne cuts this to deep cover for one.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off, Travis Head strokes this towards cover.
Floats this one full and into the stumps, Travis Head is watchful and blocks this into the off side.
Bowls this slightly short and outside off, Travis Head rocks back in the crease and punches the ball down to long off for a single and will keep strike.
Devon Thomas bowls this full and into the stumps, Travis Head digs this out to the right of mid on and takes a quick single.

FOUR! Three hundreds in a row! What an exceptional player Marnus Labuschagne is turning out to be! He reaches his landmark in style. Devon Thomas bowls this full and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne creams this to deep point and gets four runs. The number one Test batter in the world for a reason!
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this back towards the bowler.
On a good length and in line with the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne looks to tuck this leg side but gets a leading edge to cover.
Bowls this short and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne pulls this towards deep square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Devon Thomas bowls this on a good length and just outside off, gets the ball to straighten after pitching. Travis Head feels for the ball and is beaten all ends up.
Roston Chase flights this one full and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne looks to slog sweep but gets an inside edge down to fine leg for a single.
Floats this one full and outside off, Travis Head leaves this one alone.
Slightly short and outside off, Travis Head rocks back and mistimes his shot to the right of the bowler.
Bowls this full and onto the pads, Travis Head pushes this towards mid on.
This is short as well and outside off, Travis Head uses the depth of the crease and knocks this to deep cover for a single.
Bowls this into the pads on a fuller length, Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards square leg.
Devon Thomas bowls this on a good length and outside off, Travis Head cuts this to the left of backward point and a half-stop allows them to take a single.
On a good length and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne knocks this straight to short cover.
Bowls this one a touch fuller and just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to drive and gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Goes full once again and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne strokes this to the wide mid off fielder.

Some interest here from the West Indies players around the bat! Devon Thomas bowls this on a good length and just outside off, the ball nips back in. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block but gets beaten on the inside edge and the ball hits the pads before going through to the keeper. The umpire remains unmoved and they do not review this.
A low full toss on off, Travis Head eases it to covers for one.
Fuller one this time, this is flicked to square leg for one.
Bowls it on middle, Travis Head defends it o the mid on fielder.
On off again, Travis Head eases it to the mid off fielder.
Bowls it slightly shorter, Travis Head punches it to covers for one.
Back of a length again, Marnus Labuschagne cuts it to point for one again.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne taps it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head eases it to the cover fielder.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Travis Head cuts it hard and through backward point for a boundary!
FOUR! Slightly shorter one, Travis Head carves it through point for another boundary!
Fuller and on off, Travis Head eases it to the fielder at covers.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head cuts it to point for one.
Fuller and wide outside off, Travis Head drives it through the covers for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to covers.
Outside off this time, Marnus Labuschagne taps it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head punches it to point for one again.
Fuller length around off, Marnus Labuschagne drills it to short mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to mid-wicket. A misfield allows he batters to take a couple.
Fuller and wide outside off, Travis Head drives it through the covers for a couple of runs.
Fuller length around off, Head defends it back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head eases it to the mid on fielder.
Good length around off, Marnus defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne eases it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one.
Outside off, this is played towards mid on.
Fuller and on off, this is defended well.
On off, defended towards mid on.
Fuller again, Travis Head eases it to the cover fielder.
Flights this one full and in line with the stumps, Travis Head clocks this back towards the bowler.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside off, Travis Head cuts this late to the point fielder.
Shape on offer straight away! Alzarri Joseph bowls this on a good length but wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone.
Strays onto the pads looking for swing and serves this on a good length. The ball goes straight on and Marnus Labuschagne clips this to deep backward square leg for a single.

Bowls this one slightly back of a length and on a leg stump line. Travis Head tucks this ball towards deep mid-wicket and they take three runs as the ball does not have the legs to reach the boundary.
On a good length and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne taps this past the point fielder and takes an easy single.
Continues bowling on a good length and just outside off. Travis Head blocks this solidly to the right of the bowler.

Delivers this on a good length as well and on an off stump line, Travis Head punches this past the outstretched right hand of the bowler and takes a couple of runs as the wide mid off fielder collects the ball.
Jason Holder goes wide in the crease and serves this full, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne taps the ball towards point.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off at 114 clicks. There is swing and Marnus Labuschagne lets this go through to the keeper.
Delivers this slightly back of a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves this alone with some exaggerated movement.
Bowls this on just outside off on a good length and gets the ball to keep its line. Marnus Labuschagne judges this well and leaves in alone.
Well outside off on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne continues to leave the ball through to the keeper.
Maiden over for Jason Holder but he did not make the batter play a single delivery! Bowls this on a good length and on the outside off stump line. Marnus Labuschagne continues to shoulder arms to it.
Alzarri Joseph bowls this full and just outside off, Travis Head clips this towards wide mid on.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside off, Travis Head cuts this towards deep backward point and some good work by the fielder restricts them to a couple of runs.
Bowls this full and in line with the stumps, Travis Head gets an inside edge towards deep backward square leg for one.
On a good length and outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone.
Bowls a full toss going down leg side. Marnus Labuschagne looks to clip this fine but misses.

FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne does not miss out this time! Brings up the 300 for Australia with a boundary. Anderson Phillip strays down leg side on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne flicks this towards fine leg and gets four runs.
On a length and outside off, slower too. Travis Head leaves it alone.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Travis Head flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Sublime. Fuller and on off, Travis Head moves across and creams it through covers for a boundary!
Another one outside off, Travis Head eases it to covers for one.
Touch fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Slightly shorter one outside off, slower too. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.

FOUR! HUNDRED UP FOR TRAVIS HEAD! Fuller and on off, Travis Head knocks it through long off for a boundary. Fifth Test ton for Travis Head!
Back of a length and on off, Travis Head eases it to mid off for one.
Bowls it outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.

Good length and outside off, Travis Head lets this one go towards the keeper.

FOUR! Excellent shot. Good length and on off, Travis Head moves across and drives it through covers for a boundary!

Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to covers for one.
Fuller one, on off. Travis Head knocks it to long on for one.
Tossed up, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it back towards the bowler.
Keeps it bowling fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid off.
Another one on off, Marnus Labuschagne knocks it to mid on for one.
Fuller and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to mid on for one.
Another fuller ball on off, Travis Head guides it to point for one.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one.
Bowls it outside off, Travis Head taps it to covers for one more.
Fuller one and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fulller ball, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket. Travis Head wanted a single but Marnus Labuschagne sends him back. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Starts with a back of a length and outside off, Travis Head lets it go.
Slightly shorter again, Travis Head taps it to point for one. 200-run partnership comes up between Travis Head and Marnus Labuschagne!
Good length angling it in, Marnus Labuschagne covers his line and blocks it out.
Bowls it down leg, Marnus Labuschagne nudges it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it well. They collect two runs.
FOUR! Finds the gap this time. Fuller and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid off.
Bowls it on off, Travis Head eases it to point for one.
This one lands down leg, Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
Good length angling it in, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Bowls it just outside leg, Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick it but misses.
Another one outside leg, Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick it but misses again.
Outside leg again as Marnus Labuschagne again misses his flick.
EDGED AND FOUR! Fuller and on off, Travis Head looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away the third man fence for a boundary!
On middle this time, Travis Head defends it solidly.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Fuller again, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Good length angling it in, Marnus Labuschagne gently flicks it to square leg for one.
Touch fuller and shaping it into the batter, Travis Head defends it to short leg.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne fends it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head fends it to point for one.
Bangs a bouncer and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne doesn't read it but ducks it in the very end.
Back of a length on the body, this is tucked down to fine leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne eases it to the off side. Dot.
Good length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it back towards the bowler.
Length ball on the pads as Marnus Labuschagne flicks this towards short mid-wicket. Dot again.
Good length angling it in, Marnus Labuschagne looks to block it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off this time, Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms at it.
Good length and on leg, Marnus Labuschagne gently flicks it to square leg for one.
Wide! A wayward bouncer and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the off side.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne fends it to short square leg. Dot.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend it but misses.
Shorter one outside leg, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Back of a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it back towards the bowler.
Length and outside off as Travis Head punches it towards short covers.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head looks to defend it but miscues it to backward point. They collect one.
Fuller and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne cuts it to backward point for one.
FOUR! Fine shot. Shorter and outside off, Travis Head uses the pace of the ball and plays an upper cut over backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! Good length this time, Travis Head slices it through backward point for another boundary!
On a length and on off, Travis Head defends it to covers.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Outside off this time as Marnus Labuschagne blocks it to short covers.
Bangs a bouncer on off, Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
Another short ball as this is pulled away towards backward square leg for one.
Shorter again, on leg. Travis Head ducks underneath it.
Back of a length and on middle, Travis Head fends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter nad outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fuller and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Good length, just outside off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the off side.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne cuts it to backward point for one.
Bowls it outside leg, Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick it but misses.
Shorter one just outside off, Travis Head looks to play an upper cut but misses.
Good length and outside off, Travis Head leaves it alone.
On a length and on leg, Marnus Labuschagne gently flicks it to backward square leg and steal two runs. Excellent running between the wickets.
Good length again, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to short mid-wicket.
Length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one.
Goes around the wicket and bowls it on a good length, Head defends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, this is again defended towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Marnus Labuschagne cuts it to point for one.
Length and outside off, Travis Head looks to drive it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces off the deck. Dot.
Outside off as this is played towards covers for one.
On a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne taps it towards the fielder at backward point.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leans and drives it but gets an outside edge past backward point for a boundary!
A low full toss angling in, Marnus Labuschagne defends it solidly.
On a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to cut it but misses.
FOUR! Fuller and on leg, Travis Head whips it just over the man at mid-wicket for a boundary!
Outside off, Travis Head knocks it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Good length and on leg, Travis Head defends it to short leg.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Travis Head times it perfectly and whips it over mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Travis Head taps it to point for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Travis Head drives it but finds the fielder at extra covers.
Outside off as this is played towards covers for one. This brings up 250 run partnership between these two!
Bowls it on off, this is defended towards the off side.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one.
Tossed-up delivery, Travis Head guides it to point for one.
Another one on off, Marnus Labuschagne nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
On a length and on off, Travis Head eases it to mid on for one.
Good length and outside leg, Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick it but misses.
On a length shaping it in, Marnus Labuschagne fends it to mid on.
Bowls it fuller and down leg, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Travis Head slaps it but finds the fielder at deep point. They cross.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it solidly.
On off this time, Marnus Labuschagne uses his feet and flicks it to mid-wicket. The ball carries a bit and lands safely. They collect one.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head drives it to covers for one.
Outside off as this is again driven towards covers for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Travis Head guides it to point for one more.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid off.
Fuller again, Marnus Labuschagne pays it towards the fielder at mid on.
On a length and on off, Travis Head steers it to backward point for one.
Slightly shorter one and on off, Marnus Labuschagne fends it to square leg for one.
Touch fuller and on off, Travis Head drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head guides it to point. Dot.
Back of a length and on off, Travis Head fends it to short mid-wicket.
Good length angling it in, Travis Head flicks it to square leg for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Travis Head lets it be.
FOUR! 150 up for Travis Head and what a way to get it. Slightly shorter one, Travis Head slaps it past covers for a boundary. He gets a standing ovation from the crowd!
On off, defended out.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head steers it to covers for one.
Outside off again, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Another one outside off, Marnus Labuschagne blocks it to short leg.
FOUR! Slightly shorter one, Travis Head plays it uppishly through backward point for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Travis Head slaps it but finds the fielder at covers.
Goes fuller again, Travis Head drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Bowls it outside off, Travis Head guides it to deep covers for one.
Fuller and on leg, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one. 150 up for the run machine!
FOUR! Outside off, Travis Head bends low and drives it past extra covers for a boundary!
Bowls it down leg, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to fine leg for a brace.
Tossed up, on off. Marnus Labuschagne taps it towards covers for one.
Bowls it on middle, Travis Head flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne plays a reverse sweep towards deep backward point. The fielder does well to stop it at the fence. They collect three runs.
On middle as this is flicked towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to square leg for a single. Devon Thomas comes into the attack now.
Good length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne taps it but finds the fielder at backward point.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne leans and drives away from the body as he gets an outside edge that flies over the diving gully fielder for a boundary!
On off again, Marnus Labuschagne drives it but finds the fielder at covers. They cross.
On a length and on off, Travis Head defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head eases it towards the fielder at covers.
Outside off this time, Travis Head steers it to point for one.
A single as this is flicked towards mid -wicket.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Bowls it down leg, Marnus Labuschagne looks to sweep it but misses.
On off, defended out.
Bowls it on leg, Marnus Labuschagne sweeps it but gets a bottom edge towards fine leg. They cross.
Fuller again, Travis Head plays it towards the fielder at mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Massive wicket for West Indies in the game. On a length and just outside off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to cut it but gets a thick outside edge. Joshua Da Silva behind the stumps reads it well and takes a sharp catch. Marnus Labuschagne departs for 163 as he walks out to a standing ovation! Cameron Green walks in next.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Devon Thomas

Commentary: Edged and it falls just short of the first slip. Fuller and outside off, Cameron Green looks to play at it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball carries to the first slip and just flaas short. They collect two.
Fuller and on middle, Cameron Green defends it to mid on.
Bowls a bouncer as Cameron Green ducks under it.
Slightly shorter and slower too, Cameron Green lets it go.
Another one outside off as this is left alone by Cameron Green.
Fuller and outside off, Travis Head leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head punches it to mid off. Dot.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards covers.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Travis Head knocks it to mid off for one.
Keeps bowling it fuller, Cameron Green defends it back towards the bowler.
On off, Cameron Green defends it solidly.
A yorker and on off, Travis Head digs it to the mid on fielder.
Good length angling it in, Travis Head defends it to mid off.
Fuller one, on middle. Travis Head eases it to mid-wicket.
On a length and outside off, Travis Head looks to drive it but gets a bottom edge as the ball rolls towards covers. Dot.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head eases it to covers.
Bowls it outside off, Travis Head knocks it to mid on for one.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it down leg, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards mid on.
Fuller one with a hint of turn, Cameron Green defends it solidly.
Outside off this time as this is defended towards covers.
Tosses it up outside off, Cameron Green steers it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, Cameron Green eases it to covers. Dot.
Fuller again, Cameron Green flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
A yorker just outside off, Cameron Green digs it to the cover fielder.
Fuller and on middle, Cameron Green eases it to point.
Bowls a yorker and just outside off, Cameron Green defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Cameron Green drives it but finds the fielder at covers. A maiden from Devon Thomas.
Bowls it on off, Head eases it to point..
Fuller and on off, Travis Head defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off, Travis Head looks to slap it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces off the deck. Dot.
On off, this is drives towards extra covers for one.
On off, defended out.
Slightly shorter one, Cameron Green fends it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head drives it to mid off for one.
Length delivery way outside off, Cameron Green leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! Bowls it fuller and outside off, Cameron Green looks to drive it but misses. A loud appeal but the finger stays down. West Indies go for a review. Fair delivery, and the Hotspot shows that there is no contact on the blade. Cameron Green is well safe.
Fuller and outside off, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
Keeps it bowling fuller, Cameron Green defends it to mid off.
Good length and outside off, Cameron Green looks to pull it but misses. That will be DINNER on Day 2.
Loops it up, outside off, Head pushes it to the off side.
Floated and full, coming in with the arm, on off. Head stays back and taps it to point.
Much fuller, wide of off. Head reaches out and plays it past mid off for a single.
Length, sliding down leg. Green tucks it to square leg.

Almost an opportunity! It is tossed up, on middle and leg. Green goes for the sweep but misses. The ball lobs to the right of the keeper off the gloves. Joshua Da Silva is a bit late to react and only gathers it on a bounce.
Tossed up, full and on off. Green defends it out.
Alzarri Joseph steams in and dishes a length ball, on off. Head blocks it out with a straight bat.
Touch fuller, Head mistimes his drive to covers.
Good-length ball, outside off. Head reaches out and cuts it behind point for just a single.

Alzarri Joseph now serves a length ball, on off stump, at almost 138 clicks. Green presses forward and blocks it into the deck. There are two slips and a gully in place for the new batter. A positive approach from West Indies.

This is a good-length ball, going down leg. Green stays back and looks to whip it behind square on the leg side but does not connect. There is some sound though and Joshua Da Silva puts in a loud appeal from behind the sticks but the umpire shows no interest.
This time Green gets some connection on a length delivery. He tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Full, attacking the stumps. Green blocks it out.
On middle and leg. Green flicks this full delivery to mid-wicket for a single.
Floats it up, on off. Head goes back and clips it to the leg side for one.

OUT! RUN OUT! Travis Head has to walk back on 175 here. He gets a standing ovation on his way back but he will be extremely guttted. Just what the doctor ordered for West Indies here. They need a couple more now with two new batters out on the crease. This is tossed up, on leg stump. Cameron Green stays back and flicks it towards fine leg. The call is for two runs initially but Green denies it after the first run. Head though still goes through but is sent back. His dive later isn't sufficient to keep him safe. The big screen shows out. Devon Thomas is the man who is quick to react in the field. Alex Carey is the new man in.
Howout: run out (Devon Thomas / Joshua Da Silva)

Commentary: FOUR! Nicely played! Alex Carey is off the mark in fine fashion. It is full, on off. Carey gets low and reverse-sweeps it behind point for four runs.
On off, blocked out.
A yorker length ball, on leg stump. Green fails to flick it away but luckily it goes past the leg pole.
Touch shorter on off. Green pushes it out to safety.
Good length, on off, angled in. Green defends it out.
A sharp bouncer, on middle, Green ducks under it.
Short this time, outside off. Green looks to cut it away but does not time it well.
Full length, on off, driven to covers.
Tossed up, on off. Carey blocks it on his front foot.
This is full and on off. Carey pushes it to covers and gets to the other end.
Quite short, outside off. Green goes back and punches it through the gap at covers. They pick three runs with ease.
On off, defended out.
Loops it up, full and on off. Carey reverse-sweeps it past backward point for a couple.
Tossed up, on off. Carey gets forward and defends it out.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Alzarri Joseph strikes this time and sends the struggling Cameron Green back to the pavilion. West Indies get their second wicket in the second session on Day 2. They are crawling back into this game now. It is a length ball, on fifth stump. Cameron Green moves across but decides to leave it in the end. Although, he is a tad late into pulling his bat away. The ball takes the inner half and goes on to rattle the stumps behind.
Howout: b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Full length, attacking the stump. Neser defends it off his back foot.
Back of a length, in the corridor of uncertainty. Neser shoulders his arms at it.
Joseph goes full this time, just outside off. Neser steps across and drives it towards cover. Although he could not find the gap.
A length ball, angled into the pads, Neser stays back and flicks it to the leg side.
On a length again, around off this time. Michael Neser goes back and works it out to safety. A successful over by Alzarri Joseph comes to an end.
On off, blocked out.
A sitfled applead! It is looped up, on off. Carey gets low and goes for the reverse-sweep. He does misses and takes a blow high on his pads.
Carey drives this full delivery into covers for a single.
Tosses it up, on middle stump. Neser gets it to mid on off the inner half.
This is sliding down leg. Neser goes back and pads it out.
Fuller and attacking the stumps. Neser blocks it out carefully.
Joseph goes full, wide of off. Carey steps forward and drives it to the man at mid off.
Alex Carey flicks this good-length ball to square leg off his hips and crosses for one.
It is full, swinging into the pads, Neser keeps his eyes on the ball and clips it to deep square leg. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it out.
Much fuller, on off. Neser strokes it into the gap at covers. They take a couple this time.
FOUR! Neser gets his first boundary of the innings. A short ball, wide of off. Neser stands tall and cuts it through the gap at backward point for four runs.
A short ball, wide of off. Neser lets it be to conclude a solid for the hosts as 9 runs come off it.
Tossed up, on off. Carey pushes it to the right of the bowler. Roston Chase gets a hand on it but parries it towards mid off. One taken.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
Slower one now, full and on off. Neser remains solid in his defense.
Tossed up, on leg, Neser defends it back to Chase.
Short and on off stump. Neser goes back and plays it to mid off.
On off, defended out. Just a single off the over.
Good length, on leg stump. Carey closes the face of the blade and gets it towards mid on.
It is full, wide outside off. Carey times his drive well but only to find the sweeper cover. One taken.

LEG BYE! Ouch! Neser takes a blow on his helmet. It is an off-cutter, on a shorter length that skidds on off the deck. Neser tries to pull it away but misses and gets pinged on the side of his helmet. The batters still are able to collect a leg bye before Neser gets some attention from the physio.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, on off, defended with straight bat.
A short ball this time, on middle. Carey ducks under this one without any hesitation.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Neser comes across and flicks it down to long on for one.
Tossed up, around off. Carey gets forward and plays it towards backward point.
FOUR! Alex Carey just loves playing the reverse-sweep. It is full, on off. Carey gets low and reverse hits it past backward point for four runs.
On off defended out.
Fuller, on off. Carey blocks it back to the bowler.
A dot to end the over. Angles it in on leg, Carey drives it back to the bowler.
A length ball, on top of off. Neser tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full length, on middle and leg. Neser clips it through square leg for two runs.
Short and outside off. Neser stands tall and mistime his cut towards covers. The fielder there dives to his right and makes a half stop. One taken.
Length ball, on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Phillip goes full this time, wide of off. Carey leans in and pushes it to covers for a single.
FOUR! A good-looking shot! Back of a length, on off. Neser reads it early, swivels on the back foot and pulls it through the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, angled down leg. Carey stays back and clips it to short leg.
Outside off, pushed towards covers.
Touch short, on off, Carey uses the depth of the crease to deal with it.
On off, defended back to the bowler.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Carey blocks it into the deck.
This is quicker, attacking the pads. Carey fails to work it to the leg side and gets pinged on his pads. Going down leg though.
A length ball, on top of off. Neser stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Good length, outside off. Neser tries to hit it through the line but gets an inner half.
Length ball, wide of off. Neser knocks it to the man at extra cover.
Back of a length, wide outside off. Neser stands tall and cuts it to backward point for a single.
Alex Carey knocks this length delivery to point but straight to the fielder.
Full length, on off stump. Carey hangs back and blocks it away.
Angled into the pads, Neser works it to mid on.
This one is turning down leg. Neser gets it to square leg off the top of the blade.
BYE! It is tossed up, going down leg. Neser misses his flick and so does the keeper. The batters collect a leg bye.
This is flicked to the leg side for one.
On off, defended out.
Full and on off, Neser blocks it off his front foot.
FOUR! Top class! Alex Carey is making his intentions clear here. It is a short ball, on off. Carey stays back and whips it over mid-wicket for an incredible boundary.
Touch fuller, on off, Carey dabs it out.
A length ball, on fifth stump. Carey stays back and dabs it down to point for one.
Michael Neser strokes this length delivery towards deep point. Only one taken.
Fuller in length, wide of off. Carey leans in and drives it to the fielder at extra covers.
Length ball, sliding down leg. Carey tucks it behind square on the leg side for one.
On off, defended out.
A single now as this is driven to covers.
Touch short, outside off. Neser stays back and punches it through point. They take a single.

OUT! LBW! Kraigg Brathwaite appeals for lbw and the umpire raises his finger in a flash. Michael Neser thinks it is pitching outside leg and takes the review. The delivery is full and around middle, coming in with the arm. Neser looks to sweep it away but misses and takes a blow on his pads.
