The Snicko confirms that there is clear day-light between bat and ball. The Ball Tracking later confirms that it is umpire's call on ball hitting the wickets. Australia don't lose a review here but surely lose their man. Mitchell Starc is the new man at the crease.
Howout: lbw b Kraigg Brathwaite

Commentary: Mitchell Starc gets off the mark instantly as he drives this full delivery to long on for one.
Tossed up, turning down leg. Carey flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, wide of off. Carey hangs back and cuts it through point for one run.
Anderson Phillip comes 'round the wicket and angles a full delivery into the pads. Starc stays inside the crease and glances around the corner for a single.
Much fuller, on middle and leg. Carey whips it to the right of short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Up and over! Back of a length, on off. Carey stands tall and heaves it across the line for a boundary at deep mid-wicket. He moves to 30 now.
A length ball, at 134 clicks, outside off. Carey leans in and times it well. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it out. Carey wanted the third run but was sent back in no time.

Anderson Phillip very nearly gets a wicket here. A length ball, wide of off. Carey decides to play it late and hangs his blade away from his body. The ball takes the outside edge but does not carry to the man at first slip.
On off, blocked out.
Full and on off, Starc pushes it out.
Loops it up, on middle and leg. Starc flicks it to the left of mid on and crosses. This also brings up 500 for the Aussies.
Another single now as this is flicked to mid on.
Loops it up, on off, defended out.
Much fuller, attacking the pads. Starc hangs back and clips it through mid-wicket for two runs.
FOUR! Incredible shot! It is full, wide of off. Carey leans in and drives it on the up. The ball races through the gap at covers for four runs.
Alex Carey stays back to this full delivery and nudges it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Alex Carey gets his second boundary of the over and moves into 40s. Joseph goes full, on fourth stump. Alex Carey belts it past mid off. It races away.
It is full, wide of off. Alex Carey throws the kitchen sink at it but connects with thin air. He is having a go here, with the shadows coming into play now.
Back of a length, outside off. Carey lets it be.
Fuller, on off, driven to covers. Three dots on the trot to end the over. The signal comes from the pavilion and Mitchell Starc and Carey are running off the field here. Australia declare at 511-7.
Starc starts with a short ball, this one lands on middle and angles into the batter. Kraigg Brathwaite stays back and flicks it to the leg side.
Now a full one, sliding across the right-hander. Kraigg Brathwaite has no shot to offer.
Starc serves it full this time, around off and gets it back in. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it back to the bowler watchfully.

FOUR! This should settle some nerves. It is much fuller, wide of off. Kraigg Brathwaite leans in and drives it through covers. Marnus Labuschagne gives it a chase but in vain as the ball wins the race.
A single now, as Kraigg Brathwaite tucks this length delivery to square leg.
A huge appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. It is a length ball, around off, moving away. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets squared up this time.and takes a blow high on his pads.

Scott Boland starts with a beauty. A length ball, this one lands outside off and nips in off the deck. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and looks to flick it away but misses. He takes a blow above his pads. There is a loud appeal for lbw but the umpire denies.
Length ball, on off, this is punched through covers for two runs.
Good-length ball, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite hangs his blade away from his body and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length, on off, defended out.
A short ball, wide of off, this one flies off the deck. Kraigg Brathwaite shuffles across and leaves it alone.
An inswinger this time, full and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets it to mid on off the inner half.
Good length, on leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets across and blocks it out to the leg side.
Much fuller, sliding down leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul goes back and eases it to mid on.
Full length, swinging away late. Tagenarine Chanderpaul opens the face of the blade and guides it down to third man for two runs. He gets off the mark now.

NOT OUT! Tagenarine Chanderpaul makes it back into the crease safely. It is full, on off, shapes away a touch. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets it down to third man off the outer half. The batters call for the second run which could have been risky but there is no damage done in the end.
Full length, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul stays back and blocks it into covers for one.
On off, defended out.
A length ball, on off, jags back into the batter. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets rapped high on his pads.
This is on a length, outside off, shaping away. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it it be.
Fuller and on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pushes it to point with soft hands and scampers across for a quick single.
This is swinging into the batter, on a fuller length. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it out solidly.
On the pads, flicked to square leg.
Good length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to chase it but misses.
BEATEN! This is a pace up delivery. On a length, on fourth stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to block it inside the line and gets beaten.
Very full, down the leg side. Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it to deep square leg and gets to the other end.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, angled across the right-hander. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go to the keeper.
Much fuller, wide outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets low and tries to reach out but misses it this time.
Mitchell Starc serves a full-length ball, shaping back off the deck. Kraigg Brathwaite jams it out solidly. That will be TEA on Day 2.
Scott Boland starts with a length ball from 'round the wicket. This one straightens up a bit. Tagenarine Chanderpaul misses his block and gets beaten on the outside edge.
A length ball, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul dabs it down to the man at gully.
Boland now angles it into the batter, on a length. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it out watchfully.
Much fuller, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it out solidly.
Boland goes full again, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul leans in and drives it through the gap at covers for two runs.
Length ball, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it to point with an angled bat.
Starc goes full, on leg, gets some shape on it as it goes down leg. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to glance it around the corner but misess.
On a length, angling across the right-hander. Kraigg Brathwaite has no shot to offer.
A length ball, wide of off, shaping away. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone for the keeper.
Much fuller, wide outside off, nips in a touch. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it be.
Mitchell Starc serves it full, attacking the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite hangs back and blocks it out watchfully.
A dot to end the over and with that Starc records his first maiden of the innings. It is a length ball, attacking the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite goes back and nudges it to short mid-wicket.
It is full, wide of off, skidds through. Tagenarine Chanderpaul watches it sail past him.
This one is swinging into the batter, on the pads. Tagenarine Chanderpaul stays back and clips it to the leg side.
Good length, outside off, nips away off the deck. Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Good leave! A length ball, in the channel, shaping in a touch. Tagenarine Chanderpaul keeps his eyes on the ball and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Five dots in a row! Outside off, left alone.
Length, on off, pushed to covers.
Good length, angling across the right-hander. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Another one shaping away from the right-hander. Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders his arms at it.

FOUR! EDGY! Kraigg Brathwaite has the ladyluck on his side here. It is fuller, wide of off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets forward and looks to drive it through covers. The ball though takes a thick outside edge and goes past gully into the ropes at third man.
Touch short, around the hips, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to fine leg and crosses.
Fuller, on the pads, Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it to deep square leg. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it out.
This is outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Neser start with a full one, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets his blade down in time and pushes it to the off side.
Two dots to start with! This is a peach of a delivery. On a length, outside off, jags in a bit. Kraigg Brathwaite is beaten as the ball zips past the outside edge.
Length ball, nipping back in from outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite covers his stumps and nudges it to the leg side.
Full, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite eases it to mid on.
Five dots in a row! It is full, around off, shaping away a touch. Kraigg Brathwaite dabs it down towards gully.
Michael Neser starts his spell with a maiden over. A length ball, on top of off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it out watchfully.
Fuller and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it to square leg for one.
Good length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to point. The fielder does well to stop it. Dot.
On off again, Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to deep covers. The fielder cases it well. They collect three runs.
Slightly shorter and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go.
Fuller and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to covers for one.
Fuller and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back towards the bowler.
Shorter and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go.
On a length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to covers. The fielder does well to stop it. Dot.
On a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Good length, down leg. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the leg side.
Another one on leg, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to backward square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the off side and takes a single.
On off again, Tagenarine Chanderpaul eases it towards point.
Good length and just outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to defend it but misses. Close!
Another one on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it to mid off.
This one lands just outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
On off again, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it to mid off.
On a length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Fuller in length just outside off stump as Tagenarine Chanderpaul drives it down the ground. Marnus Labuschagne has a long chase to do. The batters collect three runs.
Full and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it solidly.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! On a length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to block it but misses as the ball moves a hint away and takes the outside edge of the blade. Alex Carey reads it well and takes it comfortably behind the stumps. The skipper makes his way back into the hut.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Michael Neser

Commentary: Length ball outside off stump as the batter leaves it alone here.
A touch fuller in length outside off stump as the batter defends it towards covers. Dot again.
Good length shaping it away, Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Good length and just outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to defend it but misses. Close!
Outside off again, Tagenarine Chanderpaul shoulders arms at it.
Good length again, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
On a length angling it in, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it solidly.
A maiden for Scott Boland as this is defended back towards him.
Shorter and on off, Shamarh Brooks doesn't read it well and gets a hit on his shoulder. Dot.
Bowls it on leg, Shamarh Brooks flicks it to square leg for a double.
Touch full and on off, defended well.
Fuller one again, Shamarh Brooks knocks it through mid on as they collect two runs.
Bowls it on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to play at it but gets an inside edge as the ball hits his pads and bounces off the deck. Dot.
Fuller and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul taps it to the cover fielder.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Shamarh Brooks shoulders arms at it.
Good length shaping it in, Shamarh Brooks defends it to short covers.
On a length and just outside off, Shamarh Brooks leaves it alone.
Serves it fuller, on off. Shamarh Brooks moves across and defends it to covers.
Another dot ball as this is played towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller in length on off stump as Brooks gently times it down the ground and collects three runs.
Bowls it outside off and Shamarh Brooks shoulders arms at it.
On a length and on off, Shamarh Brooks defends it solidly.
Fuller and on off, Shamarh Brooks looks to defend it but gets an outside edge. It doesn't carry to slip and Shamarh Brooks gets a lucky escape.
Good length angling in, Shamarh Brooks looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Dot.
Another dot ball as Shamarh Brooks leaves this one alone towards the keeper.

Dropped! So close. Fuller and on off, Shamarh Brooks looks to knock it but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and carries towards Michael Neser. He looks to grab onto it but just manages to get a hand on it. Close!
Full and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul steers it to backward point for a brace.
Fuller and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Good length and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it solidly.
Fuller one angling it in, Tagenarine Chanderpaul eases it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Shamarh Brooks defends it back towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Australia get their second of the day and West Indies need to work their way back into the game. On a length and just outside off, Shamarh Brooks looks to block it but misses and gets the slightest of the edge. Alex Carey behind the stumps makes no mistake and Shamarh Brooks makes his way back into the hut.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Michael Neser

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
On off as Jermaine Blackwood guides it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it to short mid-wicket and scampers through for a single.
Bowls it on off as this is defended towards mid off.
Tossed up, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it to short leg.
Bowls it outside off with a hint of turn, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to block it but misses.
Fuller one this time, this is defended back towards Nathan Lyon.
Slightly shorter one, Tagenarine Chanderpaul cuts it to point. The fielder stops it well. They collect one.
Tossed up, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood defends it solidly.
Another one on middle as this is again defended back towards Nathan Lyon.
On a length with some extra bounce, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to defend it but misses.
Another one just outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to defend it but misses again.
Slightly shorter one, Tagenarine Chanderpaul fends it to square leg.
Shorter and outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to pull it but misses.
Bowls it outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves the harmless delivery.
Another one outside off as this is left alone again. A maiden for Mitchell Starc.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Nathan Lyon gets his first of the night. Over the wicket, fuller in length and delivers it outside off. Jermaine Blackwood sits down on one knee and looks to play at it but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and carries towards Nathan Lyon as he takes a good catch. West Indies lose their third wicket!
Howout: c & b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Devon Thomas defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one as this is again defended towards Nathan Lyon.
On off this time, Devon Thomas defends it to short leg.

Oh, this was close! Fuller with some turn as it nips back in. Devon Thomas looks to drive it but misses. The ball gaps between his bat and the pads and just misses the leg pole. There was a bit of inside edge as the ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters collect three runs.
Fuller and on off, this is defended well.
Shorter and outside off, Devon Thomas leaves it alone.
Fuller length angling across outside the off. Thomas leaves it alone to the keeper.
Another one outside off as this is left alone again.
An outswinger outside off, Devon Thomas shoulders arms at it.
Good length angling it in, Devon Thomas defends it solidly.
On a length and outside off, Devon Thomas shoulders arms at it.
Tossed up with some turn, Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
SIX! Fuller nad on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets on his knee and slog sweeps it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum!
Fuller and on middle, defended solidly.
Bowls it on middle, Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it back towards Nathan Lyon.
Quicker one on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul slaps it but finds the fielder at covers.
On middle this time, Tagenarine Chanderpaul eases it back towards the bowler.
Full length, wide of off, angling across. Thomas has no shot to offer.
JAFFA! It is a short ball, in the channel, no movement this time. Devon Thomas looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Swing and a miss! Full length, wide outside off. Thomas looks to go for the booming drive but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. Mitchell Starc asking the right questions here.
Shorter, outside off. Thomas lets it be.

A length ball, around off. Thomas gets on his front foot, opens the face of the blade and works it past point with soft hands. Cameron Green gives a chase and stops it just before the ropes. The batters run three.
Back of a length, on fourth stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets behind the line and defends it out watchfully.
Floated and full, on off. Thomas whips it through mid-wicket. The batters take three this time.
Tossed up, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out.
Loops it up, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
Quicker and full, on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it to short leg.
BYE! Misses everyone. Flatter, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to cut it away but misses. It goes to fine leg after hitting Carey behind the sticks. The collect a bye.
Going down leg, left alone.
Fuller, on the pads, Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it over mid-wicket for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length, on off, blocked out.
This is short, around the hips. Thomas hops and nudges it to the leg side.
Four dots in a row to end the over! It is a short ball, angling across the right-hander. Devon Thomas leaves it alone.
Good length, wide of off, nipping in late. Tagenarine Chanderpaul though leaves it without any hesitation.
A length ball, angled in on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul squares up and gets it to point off the outer half.
Full length, on off stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets his blade down in time and blocks it to covers.
Tap and run! Very good from Tagenarine Chanderpaul. It is a length ball, on off, Chanderpaul dabs it down to point and scampers across for a quick single.
It is full, swinging into the pads, Devon Thomas blocks it out with a straight bat.
A single to end the over as Thomas knocks this length ball towards point and scampers across.
Good length, outside off. Thomas stays back and shoulders his arms at it.
Length, on off, pushed to covers.
FOUR! EDGED! A full-length ball, wide of off. Devon Thomas goes after it and manages to get a thick outside edge. It flies over the slip cordon and races away to the third man fence.
On off, played to covers.
A huge swing and a miss! It is a half-volley, wide of off. Devon Thomas looks to go after it but is a tad late into his shot.
Good length, on the hips, Thomas flicks it to the leg side.
A length ball, around off, angled across the left-hander. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to block it inside the line but misses it completely.
This time Boland attacks the off pole with a length ball. Chanderpaul pushes it out to safety.
A length ball, close to the body, Tagenarine Chanderpaul stays back and defends it to the off side.
Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends this length ball solidly.
Boland dishes a length ball, landing on middle and moving away. Tagenarine Chanderpaul shuffles and blocks it solidly with full-face of the blade.
On a length again, around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets it to point.

Almost! A length ball, outside off, shaping away a touch. Devon Thomas looks to play it without any footwork and gets a thick outside edge. Fortunately for him, it meet David Warner on a bounce at first slip.
On the pads, flicked to the leg side.
Touch fuller, on off. Devon Thomas goes back and blocks it into the deck.
Around off, defended to point.

A loud appeal for caught behind but the umpire disagrees. Steven Smith is quite interested and he takes the review. It is a length ball, on off, nipping away a touch. Devon Thomas looks to drive it away but misses. Alex Carey gathers it and puts in a loud appeal the slip cordon joins in as well. The Snicko confirms that there is no bat on it, as it comes off the pads. Later, Australia lose a review and Devon Thomas gain some more time at the crease.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Devon Thomas defends it to covers. A maiden for Neser this time.
FOUR! Green starts off with a loosener. It is a short ball, wide outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul rides the bounce well and cuts it over point for a boundary.
Short ball, once again. Tagenarine Chanderpaul swivels on his back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, on the pads, Thomas flicks it to deep square leg for one. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.

FOUR! Incredible shot! Back of a length, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pulls it in front of the man at mid-wicket. He hits it along the ground as well to fnd the boundary. Another no ball for overstepping.
A single now as Tagenarine Chanderpaul mistimes his pull to deep square leg.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is fuller, wide of off. Thomas leans in and carves it behind point for four runs.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! West Indies lose their fourth wicket now. Cameron Green strikes and finds an important breakthrough here. Australia are on top in this game. It is a length ball, on fourth stump. Devon Thomas tries to chase it but without any foot movement. He ends up dragging it on his own stumps. Cameron Green has turned this expensive over into a fruitful one. Anderson Phillip is the new man at the crease now.
Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary: Back of a length, on fifth stump, left alone.
A length ball, on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul is solid in his defense.
FOUR! Up and over! It is much fuller, angled across the left-hander. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets under it and lofts it over covers for an exceptional boundary.
Fraction short, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul cuts it to sweeper cover for one.
Fuller in length, on off. Anderson Phillip blocks it behind point.
Neser goes full yet again, on off. Phillip gets it to mid-wicket off the inside edge.
Good length, wide of off. Anderson Phillip steps forward and shoulders his arms at it.
Tagenarine Chanderpaul mistimes his pull shot this time to square leg.
Green dishes a sharp bouncer, on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul ducks under it safely.

In the air, but it lands safely! It is a short ball, on the bodyline. This one gets big on Chanderpaul. He gets a thick outside edge and the ball flies towards fine leg. The two fielders in the deep try to converge but it lands in between them.
Outside off, left alone. The umpire signals a no ball for overstepping.
A single now as this is flicked behind square on the leg side.
A dot now as this length ball is played towards mid-wicket.
A short ball, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pulls it hard to mid-wicket. Marnus Labuschagne kills the pace by getting a hand on it. The batters take one.
Back of a length, on fourth stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul dabs it down to third man for one. 100 is up for the visitors now.
It is full, on middle and leg. Anderson Phillip defends it to mid on.
Anderson Phillip leaves this length ball with ease as this is sliding down leg.
Good length, outside off, this one nips in off the deck. Anderson Phillip defends it out solidly.
Much fuller, outside off, gets no shape on this one. Anderson Phillip looks to defend it inside the line and gets beaten.
Fuller, attacking the stumps. Anderson Phillip presses forward and blocks it out.
A short ball, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pulls it hard to the leg side. Travis Head takes a blow over his knees here and allows the batters to only cross for one.
Cameron Green goes full, on middle and leg. Anderson Phillip gets his blade down in time. Another no ball for Green. He needs to be careful with his landing.
A length ball, that lands outside off and jags back in a long way. Anderson Phillip shoulders his arms at it and takes a blow near his waist.
Fuller, on off. Anderson Phillip presses forward and blocks it out.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Anderson Phillip defends it out solidly.
A sharp bouncer on middle. Anderson Phillip ducks under it safely.
A length ball, wide of off. Anderson Phillip negotiates the final delivery by defending it into the deck. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Starts with a shorter one outside leg, Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go.
Good length and on leg as he comes 'round the wicket, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it to square leg.
Bangs a shorter one, Tagenarine Chanderpaul ducks underneath it.

OUT! RUN OUT! A huge mix-up and Tagenarine Chanderpaul has to make his way back into the hut. A perfect start for Australia. On a length and on off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul taps it to the leg side and calls for one but Anderson Phillip sends him back from half way. Mitchell Starc is quick enough to get towards the ball as he makes a direct hit. The decision is sent upstairs. Replay shows that Tagenarine Chanderpaul was just out of his crease and Australia have an early breakthrough right at the start of Day 3! Jason Holder walks in next.
Howout: run out (Mitchell Starc)

Commentary: Good length and on off, Jason Holder defends it back towards the bowler.
Outside off this time, Jason Holder taps it towards the off side. Nathan Lyon to bowl from the other end.
Slightly shorter one with some turn, Anderson Phillip looks to defend it but the ball hits his thigh.
Similar to the last delivery as this again hits his pads and lobs towards the fielder at short leg.
Outside off this time, Anderson Phillip leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it solidly.
Tosses it up outside off, Anderson Phillip leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it solidly off his front foot.
Good length and outside off, slower too. Jason Holder shoulders arms at it.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT BEHIND! A slower one and outside off shaping it away, Jason Holder looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball carries behind the stumps. Alex Carey is aware of it and takes an excellent catch diving to his right. A dream start for Mitchell Starc and Australia here an they have two early wickets inside the first three overs!
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Good length and on leg, Joshua Da Silva flicks it to backward square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it towards mid off.
Goes fuller this time, on off. Anderson Phillip defends it to mid off.
Slower one outside off, Anderson Phillip leaves it alone.
Bowls it outside off turning it in, Joshua Da Silva makes a tight leave.
Another one outside off as this is defended towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and outside off turning it in, Joshua Da Silva looks to play at it but gets an inside edge as the ball passes through the stumps and rolls towards fine leg. They batters collect two.
Fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva defends it to short leg.
Slightly shorter one as this is defended towards Nathan Lyon.
A dot ball to end the over. Fuller and on the stumps as Joshua Da Silva tucks it to the short leg fielder.
On a length and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip knocks it to mid off for one.
On a length and on leg, Joshua Da Silva defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Joshua Da Silva flicks it in the gap and through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Slightly shorter one, on off. Joshua Da Silva fends it to point.
Good length shaping it away, Joshua Da Silva taps it to covers for a brace.
Fuller one with a hint of turn, Anderson Phillip looks to defend it but misses.
SIX! Bowls it fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip gets on his knee and slog sweeps it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie!
Outside off turning it in, Anderson Phillip looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip drills it through mid off for a boundary!
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it to mid on.
On a length and outside off, Joshua Da Silva defends it to mid off.
Slower one nad on middle, Joshua Da Silva defends it back towards the bowler.
Goes fuller, Joshua Da Silva nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Good length angling it in, Joshua Da Silva tucks it to square leg for one.
Bangs a bouncer, Anderson Phillip ducks under it.
On a length and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it to the fielder at gully.
Slightly shorter one, Joshua Da Silva eases it to mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Joshua Da Silva punches it to deep covers. The fielder chases it well. They collect three runs.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip drills it down the ground and over Nathan Lyon for a boundary!
Goes fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it to mid on.
Bowls it down leg, Anderson Phillip leaves it as the ball hits his pads.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip slog sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Good length and on off, Joshua Da Silva defends it solidly.
Bowls it just outside off, Joshua Da Silva looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva guides it through point for a boundary!
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Fuller and on off again, Joshua Da Silva flicks it in the gap through mid-wicket for a boundary!
On off this time as this is defended towards the fielder at point.
Fuller one again, Joshua Da Silva defends it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip eases it to mid on.
Fuller again, Anderson Phillip knocks it to mid on for one.
Bowls it on off, Joshua Da Silva blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Joshua Da Silva defends it to the fielder at short leg.
Another one on off, Joshua Da Silva defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off with some turn, Joshua Da Silva looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it towards mid off.
Outside off this time, Anderson Phillip lofts it over covers. The fielder has a long chase to do. The batters collect three runs.
Good length and outside off, Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone.
Fuller one and on off, Joshua Da Silva eases it to mid off.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva blocks it back towards the bowler.
On a length and just outside off, Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone.
Bowls it on off with some turn, Anderson Phillip eases it to mid off.
Another one on off, Anderson Phillip eases it to mid off.
Bowls it on off, Anderson Phillip defends it to mid off again.
Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it back towards the bowler.
Fullish on the middle. Anderson Phillip lunges and defends it back to Nathan Lyon.
Fuller and on middle, Anderson Phillip flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! On off, Anderson Phillip drills it down the ground and over Scott Boland for a boundary!
Outside off, Anderson Phillip pulls it to square leg for a brace.
Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Good length and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it solidly.
This one lands just outside off, Anderson Phillip looks to defend it but misses. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Fuller one and on off, Anderson Phillip knocks it to mid off and calls for a quick single. The fielder has a shy but misses. Close!
Tossed up, on off. Anderson Phillip defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Anderson Phillip gets on his knee and slogs it over mid-wicket for a boundary!
Another one on middle, Anderson Phillip defends it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, Anderson Phillip defends it back towards Nathan Lyon again.
Bowls it on off, Anderson Phillip blocks it to short leg.
Fuller and on off, Anderson Phillip defends it to short leg again.
Good length angling it in, Joshua Da Silva defends it solidly.
Goes fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva opens the face of the bat and pats it to short point.
Fuller again, Joshua Da Silva flicks it but finds the fielder ta mid-wicket.
Shorter one outside off, Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone.
Bowls it on off, Joshua Da Silva looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards the leg side. They cross for a leg bye.
Fuller one and on off, Anderson Phillip eases it to the fielder at mid on.
Lyon starts this over with a googly and Joshua Da Silva blocks it off watchfully.

OUT! LBW! Nathan Lyon puts in a loud appeal for lbw but it is turned down. Steven Smith and company though seems to be interested and the review is taken. Coming to the delivery, it is tossed up, around off. It grips and turns in. Joshua Da Silva goes back inside the crease to flick it away but takes a blow high on his pads. The Snicko confirms that there is no bat involved. The Ball Tracking shows three reds and Joshua Da Silva's innings comes to an end. He trudges back to pavilion. West Indies slip even further now.
Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Fuller and on off. Chase pushes it to covers for a single. He gets off the mark.
Full yet again, attacking the stumps. Phillip gets it to the leg side off the inner half.
A single now as this is driven down the ground towards long off.
Pushed through quicker, full and on off. Chase drives it to the man at extra cover.
Boland bends his back hard and dishes out a bouncer at 132 clicks. Anderson Phillip wisely ducks under this one.
Quite full, angled into the pads, Anderson Phillip nudges it to the leg side.

In the air but safe! It is a length ball, around off. Anderson Phillip gets on his front foot and looks to drive it through the line. The ball lofts over covers and lands safely. The batters take a couple.

Fuller, on off, Phillip lofts it over mid on this time. It is long chase for the fielder and hence the batters decide to take three. The third run could've turned to be a risky one if Marnus Labuschagne would've hit the stumps at the non-striker's end, as he gathers the throw from the deep but fails to have any contact with the stumps.
On off, defended out.
Fuller in length, attacking the stumps. Chase blocks it out watchfully. Scott Boland is still hunting for a wicket here.
Floated and full, on off. Anderson Phillip defends it out on his front foot.
A googly now on a fuller length, Anderson Phillip pushes it out to safety.
Loops it up, full and outside off. It grips and turns in. Anderson Phillip gets rapped high on his pads.
On off, defended out carefully.
Fuller, on off. Phillip plays it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, around off, this one turns into the batter. Anderson Phillip tries to defend it but it almost carries to the man at short leg. A maiden for Lyon.
Chase stays back and shoulders his arms at this length delivery as it is wide outside off.
Length and on off, Chase knocks it towards covers.
A quick single this time. An inswinging delivery, full and on off. Chase blocks it into the deck and scampers across for a quick single.
Good length, outside off. Anderson Phillip lets it be.
Slightly full, on middle and leg. Anderson Phillip shuffles and pushes it towards mid on.

OUT! RUN OUT! Comedy of errors out in middle and Australia do benefit from it. West Indies lose another wicket here. It is a full-length ball, outside off. Anderson Phillip looks to drive it through the line but does so uppishly. It lands just short of the fielder at covers. Anderson Phillip thinks he could sneak in a single here and ventures out of the crease looking for one. Marnus Labuschagne though is quick to charge in from the deep and is alert enough to through it towards the striker's end as Anderson Phillip found himself in no man's land. Phillip tried to get back but could not do in time as Alex Carey was on the money with his throw from a few meters out.
Howout: run out (Marnus Labuschagne / Alex Carey)

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Roston Chase defends it to mid off.
Another one on off as this is defended towards the bowler.
Outside off this time, Roston Chase looks to defend it but the ball hits his pads and lobs towards the slips.
Tossed up, on middle. Roston Chase pushes it to mid on for one.

OUT! LBW! Another one bites the dust. Tosses it up on middle, Alzarri Joseph looks to block it but misses. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Alzarri Joseph goes upstairs. Fair delivery, Ultra edge shows no spike. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Alzarri Joseph makes his way back into the hut for a golden duck! Marquino Mindley walks in.
Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: On off, blocked out.
Fuller, on off stump. Chase blocks it out watchfully.
Good length, outside off. Chase lets it be.
Much fuller, swinging into the pads, Chase gets inside the line and flicks it to wide of long on for a single.
It is full, around off. Mindley opens the face and guides it towards the man at gully.
An in-tucker this time, full and on off. Mindley blocks it on his front foot.
A full-length ball, on off. Mindley looks to flick it away but only manages to find a leading edge. It lobs and lands safely at point. The batters cross for one. Mindley will retain the strike.
It is tossed up, around off, turning a long way down leg. Mindley pads it to short leg.
Fuller and on leg, Mindley once again pads it out.
Quicker and fuller, on fourth stump. Mindley goes for the drive but gets it to square leg off the inside edge.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
It is tossed up, full and on leg. Mindley gets it to square leg off the inner half.
Lyon records his third maiden now. It is full and on off. Mindley defends it into the off side.
Full length, on middle and leg, blocked out towards mid on.
This time Boland goes full, attacking the pads, Chase clips it past mid on but does not opt for a run.
Back of a length, on fourth stump. This one extracts some extra bounce off the deck. Chase goes on his toes to fend it out.
On off, defended out.
Fuller, on the pads, Chase flicks to deep square leg and rotates the strike.
Full and on off, defended out on the front foot.
Pushed through quicker, on off. Chase defends it out watchfully.
Full and on the pads, nudged to the leg side.
Slightly full, Chase defends it back to the bowler.
A length ball, this is turning down leg. Chase goes back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Looped up, on off, blocked out.
Slower through the air, full and on leg. Marquino Mindley nudges it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on off, defended out.
Good length, on middle and leg. Chase flicks it to mid-wicket. The umpire signals a no ball for overstepping.
On off, defended out.
Short ball, on off. Chase pulls it to mid-wicket.
This is full and on off. Chase drives it to cover but not in the gap.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Green dishes a full ball, on the pads, Chase stays back and flicks it towards fine leg. It races all the way.
Fuller, outside off. Chase steers it through backward point for a single.
Looped up, on off, pushed to covers.
On off, blocked out.
A single now as this is driven through covers.
Loops it up, wide of off. It grips and turns in. Marquino Mindley gets beaten on the inside edge as he looks to block it away.
BEATEN! It is tossed up, outside off. Marquino Mindley looks to block it away but misses.
On off, defended out on the front foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Chase leaves it alone.

FOUR! Up and over! Chase gets fortunate this time. It is a short ball, on fourth stump. Chase gets a thick outside edge and it flies towards David Warner at first slip. Warner gets a hand on it but is unable to gather it. The ball races away to the fence.
A length ball, on off, Chase blocks it out safely.
Outside off, left alone.
Short and on off, pushed to covers.
On a length and on off, Roston Chase defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, outside off. Mindley gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to defend it out.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated and full, on off. Mindley defends it out.
On off, defeneded on the front foot.
Loopy ball, on off. Mindley blocks it out watchfully.
A googly now, full and on off. Marquino Mindley presses forward and defends it out.
A length ball, on off. Chase defends it out solidly.
Touch shorter, on off. Chase keeps his eyes on the ball till the end and pushes it out to safety.
A short ball, on the body. Chase gets inside the line and flicks it to square leg at the very end.
SIX! All the way! It is a short ball, on off. Roston Chase stands tall and dispatches it over the square leg fence.
This time Chase pulls a short ball to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Through the gap! It is a full-length ball, outside off. Mindley gets it through the gap behind backward point. It races away to the boundary.
Loops it up, on off, defended out.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is tossed up, full and on off. Chase gets under it and lofts it over the off side for a boundary.
Flatter and on off. Chase is solid in his defense.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over. It is full and on off. Chase lofts it down the ground and gets a boundary yet again.
On off, defended out.
Quicker one, outside off. Chase blocks it out on his back foot.
Fulller and on off, Marquino Mindley defends it to square leg.
A yorker right into the blockhole, Marquino Mindley defends it to gully.
Slightly shorter one on middle and leg, Marquino Mindley fends it to mid on.

Dropped! Another chance and the West Indies are right on the edge here. Fuller and on off, Marquino Mindley looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball carries towards Alex Carey who makes a diving attempt to his right but misses.
SIX! Top shot. Fuller again, Marquino Mindley flicks it with his wrist over square leg for a maximum!
Good length and just outside off, Marquino Mindley looks to defend it but misses.
Tossed up, on middle. Roston Chase flicks it to mid-wicket.
Bowls it outside off, Roston Chase eases it to covers.
Fuller one on middle, Roston Chase nudges it to mid-wicket for one.

A loud appeal turned down. Fuller with some turn, Marquino Mindley looks to defend it but misses and goes towards Alex Carey. Steven Smith decides to review. Fair delivery and nothing on Hotspot and Ultra Edge. Marquino Mindley is well safe.
Another one outside off, Marquino Mindley looks to drive it but misses.
On off, defended out solidly.
On a length and on off, Roston Chase defends it to short covers.
Fuller and on off, Roston Chase drives it through covers. Marnus Labuschagne has a long chase to do which he does. The batters collect two.

OUT! TAKEN! Mitchell Starc gets the last wicket finally. Fuller and on off, Roston Chase looks to use the pace of the ball and flick it but mistimes it completely. The ball goes up in the air towards deep backward square leg. Nathan Lyon takes a good catch diving forward and West Indies are bundled out for 214 runs! That will be DINNER on Day 3.
Howout: c Nathan Lyon b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: On a length and on leg, Usman Khawaja flicks it to fine leg and gets off the mark. They collect two runs.
Slightly shorter one angling it in, Usman Khawaja doesn't read it well and leaves it in the end.
Good length and on off, Usman Khawaja defends it to mid on.
Goes fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja taps it towards the fielder at mid on.
Bowls it outside off this time, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja guides it to the fielder at covers.

FOUR! EDGY! Fuller and just outside off, David Warner looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball carries and flies past the fiving fielder at slips. It races away the third man fence for a boundary!
Good length and on off, David Warner defends it solidly.
Another one angling it in, David Warner defends it to mid off.

Touch fuller and just outside off, David Warner looks to block it but misses and gets his pads. A stifled appeal turned down. West Indies have a chat amongst themselves and decide not to review this one.
Fuller and on off, David Warner flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR LEG BYES! On a length and down leg, Usman Khawaja looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!

Slightly shorter one, David Warner awkwardly defends it. Alzarri Joseph thinks its his pads and decides to review it. Replay shows that it was a fair delivery. Nothing on Hotspot and Ultra Edge. Ball Tracking shows that it was just clipping the leg pole but the impact is the umpires call and the on field decision stands. Close!
Fuller and on off, David Warner defends it solidly.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards mid on.
FOUR! Bowls it on leg, David Warner just gives it a fine tickle as the ball races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!
Good length outside off shaping it away, David Warner leaves the harmless delivery.
Similar to the last delivery as this is again left alone by David Warner.
On a length and on middle, Usman Khawaja defends it solidly.
FOUR! Excellent placement. Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja knocks it through long off for a boundary!
On a length and on off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Fuller one and on off, Usman Khawaja eases it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter one outside off, David Warner fends it to covers.
Another one outside off, David Warner leaves it alone.
FOUR! On a length and outside off, Usman Khawaja uses the pace of the ball and guides it through backward point for a boundary!
Slightly shorter one shaping it away, Usman Khawaja looks to defend it but misses.
Outside off, Usman Khawaja taps it to the fielder at short third man. Dot.
Fuller this time, on middle. Usman Khawaja defends it back towards Alzarri Joseph.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja rocks back and guides it to the cover fielder.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja opens the face of his bat and guides it to deep point. They collect one run.
Good length and outside off, Usman Khawaja shoulders arms at it.
Touch fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja knocks it to long off for one.
On a length angling it into the batter, David Warner fends it to covers and scampers through for a single.
Outside off this time, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja guides it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, David Warner eases it to covers for one.
On a length and on off, David Warner guides it to deep covers for a brace.
Slightly shorter one, David Warner pulls it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket. Dot.
Back of a length and outside off, David Warner leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter one, David Warner fends it to covers for one.
Good length and on off, Usman Khawaja defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one on off, Usman Khawaja drives it to deep covers for one.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and on off, Usman Khawaja caresses it through covers for a boundary!
FOUR! Slightly shorter one on leg, Usman Khawaja looks to pull it but gets a bottom edge as the ball races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!
Bowls it outside off, slower too. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
On off, defended out.
On a length and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Usman Khawaja looks to pull it but misses.
Fuller and on off, David Warner defends it back towards the bowler.
Good length with some extra bounce, David Warner doesn't read it well and awkwardly pulls it to deep mid-wicket. The ball carries and lands safely. They collect one.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja taps it to covers for one.
On a length and on off, David Warner looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball rolls towards third man. They collect three runs.
Good length and on off, Usman Khawaja defends it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, Usman Khawaja eases it to mid off.
Slightly shorter one, David Warner taps it towards the fielder at covers.
Back of a length and on off, David Warner guides it to point for one.
On a length and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off, Usman Khawaja looks to slap it but gets a slight of the edge as the ball carries and just drops short of the keeper. Close!
Outside off, Usman Khawaja steers it to point for one.
Bowls it wide outside off, David Warner eases it to the point fielder.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is short, angling down leg. Usman Khawaja drags his pull shot behind square on the leg side for four runs.
Fuller in length, outside off. Usman Khawaja dabs it down to third man for a couple of runs this time.
Phillip goes full, attacking the stumps. Usman Khawaja blocks it out to safety.
On off, blocked out.
Good length, around off, defended out.
Fuller this time, on off. Usman Khawaja gets it back to the bowler off the inner half.
On a length, outside off. Warner punches it to deep point for a single.
A length ball yet again, but this attacking the pads. Usman Khawaja stays back and flicks it through square leg for two runs.
FOUR! Incredible shot! It is a short one, wide of off. Usman Khawaja goes back and cuts it late to get it through backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! Usman Khawaja is on a roll. It is a full toss, outside off. Usman Khawaja tonks it through point for another boundary.
Swing and a miss! A full toss yet again but this Usman Khawaja gets beaten as looks to drive it through the line.
A length ball, outside off, left alone.
Short and wide outside off. Warner cuts it behind point for a single.
Usman Khawaja drives this full delivery to sweeper cover for a run.
A length ball, coming in from outside off. David Warner stays back and blocks it away.
FOUR! Width on offer and Warner makes the most of it. It is on a good length, wide of off. David Warner goes back and cuts it through point for four runs.
A single now as this length ball is pushed into covers.
Back of a length, outside off. Usman Khawaja lets it sail past him. 7 runs come off the over. Australia are cruising.

It is tossed up, on off. David Warner tries to go for the reverse-sweep but misses. The ball bounces off his elbow and goes to the man at first slip. There is an appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Quite full, outside off. Warner pushes it to deep point for one.
Touch short, outside off. Usman Khawaja gets it behind point. They take three before the fielder cuts it out.
On leg, Warner flicks it to square leg.
Full and on off. Warner knocks it to wide of long on for a single.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Roston Chase comes into the attack and has an instant impact as West Indies see the back of David Warner here. Chase comes 'round the wicket and serves it full, wide of off. David Warner tries to latch onto it and slash it away but only gets a thick inside edge. The ball goes on to rattle the stumps. Will West Indies build on this wicket?
Howout: b Roston Chase

Commentary: Fuller and on off. Marnus Labuschagne knocks it down to long on for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Roston Chase gets his second wicket and both the Australian openers are back into the hut in a jiffy. This is just what West Indies needed. It is tossed up, around off, turning away a hint. Usman Khawaja only manages to get a slight outside edge. Joshua Da Silva takes a sharp catch behind the sticks. Steven Smith is the new man in.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Roston Chase

Commentary: Full toss, on leg. Steven Smith flicks it to square leg for a single.
Full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to cover for one.
On off,defended out.
Fuller, on leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg for one.
Steven Smith drives this length ball through covers for one.
Around off, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg.
On off, punched to cover.
Full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne knocks itdown to long on for two runs.
Loops it up, around off, blocked out.
This full, on leg. Steven Smith stays back and clips it through square leg for two runs.
On leg, flicked to mid-wicket.
No ball!  WOAH! Huge turn! It is tossed up, around off. it grips and turns in a long way. Steven Smith is surprised by the spin. Smith is hit on his gloves but it falls besides the man at short leg.
Tossed up, on off, defended out.
Around off, blocked it out.
Fuller, on the pads, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket for one run.
Around off, Marnus Labuschagne is solid in his defense.
Full and on off, played back to the bowler.
Full, on leg. Smith nudges it to square leg.
Touch short, outside off. Smith looks to cut it away but misses.
This is on middle and leg. Smith clips it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and quicker on the pads and Smith flicks it to mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length ball on the middle and leg and Smith nudges it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid on.
Outside off as this is played towards mid-wicket.
Goes fuller again, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Steven Smith hands back and flicks it through square leg for a boundary!
Tossed up, on off. Steven Smith eases it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller again, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne knocks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
SIX! BANG! Fuller and on off, Steven Smith gets on his knee and slogs it over mid-wicket for a maximum!
Fuller ball down the leg and Smith bends on one knee and scoops it to fine leg and collects three runs.
FOUR! Fine shot. Bowls it outside off, Marnus Labuschagne reverse sweeps it through point for a boundary!
Tosses it on muddle, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket for a brace.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne reverse sweeps it through backward point for another boundary!
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne gently flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Slightly shorter one, Steven Smith defends it to mid on.
Bowls it outside off, Steven Smith guides it to covers for one.
Another one outside off, Marnus Labuschagne punches it to deep covers for a brace.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne reverse sweeps it through third an for a boundary. Marnus Labuschagne is enjoying these reverse sweeps here!
Another reverse sweep but gets the fielder at backward point this time. They collect one.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Steven Smith sweeps it over square leg for a boundary!
Slightly shorter one outside off, Marnus Labuschagne guides it to deep backward point and collects three runs.
Good length angling it in, Steven Smith defends it solidly.
Outside off, Steven Smith taps it but finds the fielder at gully.
Goes fuller this time, Steven Smith drives it to deep covers for one.
Good length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Goes fuller and on leg, Steven Smith defends it to mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Marnus Labuschagne pulls it hard towards square leg. The fielder at the deep stops it well diving to his right. They collect two runs.

OUT! TAKEN! Anderson Phillip gets the big fish here and Marnus Labuschagne departs for 31. On a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to cut it but doesn't read it well. He gets a thick outside edge and Roston Chase at gully takes an excellent catch diving to his right. Australia is three down for 136 and that will be TEA BREAK for Day 3.
Howout: c Roston Chase b Anderson Phillip

Commentary: Slightly shorter one outside off, Travis Head leaves it alone.
Outside off, Travis Head defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Travis Head looks to pull it but misses.
Good length and outside off, Travis Head looks to play at it but misses.
DROPPED! Fuller and on off, Steven Smith looks to flick it over square leg but mistimes it completely. The ball goes in the air towards the fielder who drops a dolly. A lucky escape for Steven Smith!
Fuller and on off, Steven Smith pushes it to covers for one.
Another single as this is played towards point.
Good length angling it in, Steven Smith taps it to covers for one.
On a length and outside off, Travis Head looks to flick it but misses.
Bowls it on off, Travis Head looks to play at it but gets his pads as the ball rolls towards third man. An overthrow allows the batters to steal a leg bye.
Back of a length and on off, Travis Head eases it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head lofts it over mid on but doesn't get the power right. The fielder chases it as the batters take three runs.
Fuller and on off, Steven Smith flicks it to square leg for one.
Wide! Shorter and on leg, Travis Head looks to pull it but misses.
Slower one and on leg, Travis Head digs it to mid on for one.
Bowls it outside off, Steven Smith defends it to the gully fielder.
Fuller and on off, Steven Smith taps it to point for one.
Fuller and on off again, Steven Smith drives it to deep covers for three runs.
FOUR! A slower one and on off, Travis Head hangs back and drives it through covers for a boundary!
Bowls it outside off as Travis Head leaves this one towards the keeper.
Shorter one on off, Travis Head plays an upper cut towards short third man. The ball carries and lands safely just before the fielder. They cross.
Fuller and down leg, Steven Smith looks to flick it but misses as the ball gets his pads.
On a length and on off, Steven Smith knocks it to mid off for one.

OUT! TAKEN! Fuller and on leg, Steven Smith looks to use the pace of the ball and flick it but mistimes it completely. The ball goes up in the air towards fine leg. Devon Thomas reads the ball well and takes it comfortably. Alzarri Joseph gets his man and the skipper departs!
Howout: c Devon Thomas b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Cameron Green knocks it to mid off for one.
Touch fuller and on off, Travis Head flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Shorter one and on off, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
FOUR! Fuller one this time, Cameron Green drills it straight down the ground for a boundary!

OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust. Slightly shorter one, Cameron Green looks to pull it but mistimes it and gets a leading edge. The ball goes high up in the air and towards short covers and Kraigg Brathwaite settles under it and takes it comfortably.
Howout: c Kraigg Brathwaite b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Slower one and on off, Travis Head looks to slap it but gets a top edge. The ball flies over the keeper and towards third man. They collect two.
Fuller and on off, Travis Head knocks it to mid on for one.
Bowls it outside off, Alex Carey knocks it to the cover fielder.
Bowls it on off, Alex Carey whips it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Fuller and on off, Alex Carey flicks it to square leg for one.
Slightly shorter one and on off, Travis Head guides it towards deep backward point for one.
Fuller delivery angling into the batter, Travis Head slogs to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head looks to pull it but gets his shoulder to short fine leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Alex Carey defends it solidly.
Fuller one again, Alex Carey flicks it to deep square leg for one.
Another fuller delivery, Travis Head slaps it to point for one.
A single as this is flicked towards square leg.
Wide! Bangs a shorter one outside off, Alex Carey leaves it alone.
Slower one on off, Alex Carey pulls it to square leg for one.
SIX! Fuller and slower too, Travis Head heaves it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie!
SIX! Another slower delivery and gets the same result. Travis Head heaves it over deep mid-wicket for another maximum. The local boy is enjoying the game now!
Slightly shorter one, Travis Head taps it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, Alex Carey drives it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter and down leg, Travis Head looks to pull it but misses and gets the slightest of the edge as the keeper misses to grab it. They cross.
Yorker length, on leg. Head gets his blade down in time and flicks it to the leg side.
Short ball, outside off. Carey stays back and slaps it to deep point for one.
FOUR! Powerful shot. Short ball, outside off. Head stays back and cuts it through point for four runs.
This is pulled to mid-wicket for a single.
On off. blocked out.

OUT! TIMBER! Alzarri Joseph gets his third wicket. The seamer fires in a yorker, right in the blockhole. Alex Carey tries to flick it away but fails to get any connection. The ball goes through the gap and rattles the stumps. Australia have decided to declare now.
Howout: b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: West Indies get a run on the board through leg bye! It is a length ball, on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite fails to flick it away. The ball hits the pads and rolls out to square leg. They cross for a leg bye.

Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets off the mark with a boundary here. It is full and on off pole. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets squared up a bit and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies through the gap at slip cordon and races away to the fence.
This is on a length, outside off, shaping away. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it be.
A length ball, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul shuffles and flicks it to deep square leg for two runs.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away a touch. Tagenarine Chanderpaul does not bother chasing it.
So, 7 runs come off the first over. Shorter ball to end the over, wide of off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul keeps his bat to himself.
It is a length ball, outside off, jags back in. Kraigg Brathwaite gets pinged high on his thigh pads, meanwhile Michael Neser gets on the floor with his followthrough.
Almost drags it on! It is on a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to cut it away but it gets a thick inside edge onto his shoes.
Fuller, swinging into the pads, Kraigg Brathwaite tucks it to mid on.
Fuller, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out to covers.
On off, blocked out.
This is full, outside off, shaping away, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to chase it but misses.
This one does not carry! It is a length ball, around off, shaping away from the batter. Starc draws a healthy edge but it lands short of Warner at first slip.
On top of off, blocked out.
Good length, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out to safety.
FOUR! Up and over! Short ball, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul cuts it over point for four runs.
On off, blocked out.
Good length, around off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, on off, jags back in and hits Kraigg Brathwaite on the pads.
Length ball, on off, blocked out to safety.
It is pitched up, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it down the ground towards mid on. They take three.
Fullish ball, on middle Tagenarine Chanderpaul pushed to covers for one.
Length, blocked out solidly,
Good length, on top of off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out on his back foot.
Full ball, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets it to point.
Good length, down leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to flick it away but misses.
Length ball, just outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Four dots in a row! Length ball, on off, blocked out solidly.
A sharp bouncer, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul sways away from the line of the delivery.
This is outside off, shaping away. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it be.

OUT! An instant impact for Scott Boland. He grabs a wicket off his very first delivery. Boland serves it on a length, outside off, it shapes away a touch. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to block it away but gets a thick outside edge. Alex Carey gathers it safely.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Scott Boland

Commentary: Length ball, on off, Brooks pushes it out.

OUT! LBW! Scott Boland gets his second wicket in a blink of an eye. This is getting worse for West Indies now. Boland dishes a length ball, outside off, but gets this one to jag back in. Shamarh Brooks is caught inside his crease and gets rapped on his pads. Boland appeals and the finger goes up in a flash. Shamarh Brooks did not even think about taking the review once.
Howout: lbw b Scott Boland

Commentary: Good length and on off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it to covers.
A length ball, on off. Jermaine Blackwood gets it out to safety.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust. Scott Boland gets his third wicket. He seems to be in a hurry to end things here. It is a length ball, outside off, jags away a touch. Jermaine Blackwood looks to go after it but only finds a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards Green at gully at a very low height and Green does a tremendous job in getting low and taking a sharp catch.
Howout: c Cameron Green b Scott Boland

Commentary: A length ball, on the pads, Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it to square leg for one.
Too full, on off, pushed to covers.
Full again, outside off. Thomas looks to chase it but misses.
Good length, wide of off, shaping away. Thomas leaves it alone.
A length ball, this one lands outside off and jags back in to hit Devon Thomas on the flap on his pads. But it is too high as he was even hoping in the crease at the same time.
Outside off, wide of off. Thomas has no shot to offer.
Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends this length ball back to the bowler.
On a length, wide of off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
On middle and leg, this is flicked to the leg side.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is a short ball, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul stays back and cuts it through square leg for four runs.
Outside off, left alone.
A single to end the over as this is played to square leg.
This is outside off, shaping away a touch. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it be.

Almost carries! It is a length ball, around off, shaping away a touch. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets a thick outside edge but because he plays it with soft hands it does not carry to Usman Khawaja in the slip cordon.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! It is a full-length ball, angling down leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to flick it away but misses. Alex Carey appeals but the umpire seems to be uninterested. Australia seem to be keen and they take the review. The Hotspot later confirms that the bat is involved and West Indies are four down for just 21 runs. They are in a spot of bother here. Jason Holder is the new man in.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Outside off, left alone.
Good length, on off. Holder defends it out.
This is full, outside off. Holder leaves it alone.
A length ball, straying on the pads, Thomas nudges it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, outside off. Thomas blocks it through the line.
A length ball, on off. Thomas defends it to covers.
Good length, wide of off. Thomas looks to defend it out but misses.
BEAUTY! A length ball, on fourth stump. This one holds its line and Thomas gets beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend it out.
Boland gets his second maiden. It is a length abll, wide of off. Thomas has no shot to offer.
On a length and on off, Jason Holder defends it solidly.
Outside off this time, Jason Holder leaves it alone.
Goes fuller this time, Jason Holder looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge towards slips. Dot.
Good length angling in, Jason Holder flicks it to square leg for one.
Bowls it on off, Jason Holder taps it to mid off.
Bowls it on off shaping it away, Jason Holder plays it with soft hands towards slips.
Bowls it on off, Devon Thomas defends it to the off side.
Another one on off, Jason Holder eases it to the off side for one.
Good length and on off, Devon Thomas defends it to mid off.
On off, defended out.
Bowls it on leg, Devon Thomas looks to flick it but gets his pads towards the leg side. They cross for a leg bye.
A tad fuller ball on off, Jason Holder defends it to silly mid on.
Bowls it outside off, Devon Thomas leaves the harmless delivery.
It is full, outside off. Thomas drives it to cover.
Full length, on off. Thomas defends it out watchfully.
BEATEN! It is a length ball, outside off. Devon Thomas looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, wide of off. Thomas looks to chase it but misses.
Devon Thomas defends this length ball watchfully.
It is tossed up, around off, turning in. Holder gets hit on his waist.
Fuler, on off. Holder flicks it to the leg side.
On off, blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle. Jason Holder defends it back towards the bowler.
Another dot ball as this is again defended back towards the bowler.
Outside off with some turn, Jason Holder blocks it to short mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Devon Thomas defends it too short covers.
Fuller and on off, Devon Thomas knocks it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Touch fuller and on off, Devon Thomas knocks it straight down the ground and Michael Neser gets his had to it. Dot.
Fuller one on leg, Devon Thomas flicks it to square leg for one.
Bowls it outside off, Jason Holder eases it to short covers.
Good length angling it in, Jason Holder covers his line and defends it away.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Devon Thomas defends it with soft hands towards slips.
Goes fuller this time, Devon Thomas lunges and defends it away.
Tossed up, on middle. Devon Thomas defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Devon Thomas knocks it to long off for three runs.
Fuller and turning it in, Jason Holder defends solidly.
Tossed up, on middle. Jason Holder eases it back towards Nathan Lyon.
Slightly shorter one, Devon Thomas eases it to mid on.
Shorter and outside off, Thomas fends it to point.
Another one on off as this is defended back to the bowler.
On-off, defended.
A length ball, angled into the pads, Thomas flicks it to the leg side.
A short ball, on middle and leg. Thomas swivels and pulls it over square leg. The batters take two.
Full and on off. Holder blocks it on his front foot.
Around off, defended out.
Tossed up, on off. Jason Holder taps it to covers.
Bowls it on middle, Jason Holder defends it solidly.
Quicker and on off, Jason Holder eases it to mid off. Dot.
Flighted up on off, Jason Holder defends it towards Nathan Lyon.
Slower and outside off, Devon Thomas looks to defend it but misses.
Another one on off, Devon Thomas flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Bowls it on middle as Jason Holder defends it to mid off.
Bowls it outside off shaping it in, Jason Holder makes a tight leave.
On off again, Jason Holder flicks it to square leg for one.
Good length ball shaping in, and Devon Thomas gets beaten on the outside edge.
It is a googly, around off. Holder gets pinged on his pads.
It is tossed up, around off, turning in a touch. Holder looks to block it out but misses and gets hit on his pads.
Full and on off, blocks it out watchfully.
Holder gets pinged on his pads yet again but this is going down leg.
Outside off, turning in. Holder gets beaten on his inside edge and takes a hit on his pads. Not in line with the stumps but.
FOUR! Overpitched, on off. Holder drives it through covers for four runs.
Full length, on off, blocked out.
This is outside off, left alone.
Length ball, on off. Thomas defends it out.
Fullish around off, pushed to covers.
On off, defended out.
Fuller in length, around off, blocked to point.
Full on off, Holder looks to flick it away but misses. He takes a hit on his pads but going down leg.
Loops it up, around off. Holder blocks it on his front foot.
Flatter on the pads. Holder looks to smother it but misses.
Full attacking the stumps, blocked back to the bowler.
On off, blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Holder defends it back to the bowler. And with that it will be STUMPS ON DAY 3.

Starts with a length ball on leg, Devon Thomas looks to block it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The players decide amongst themselves and opt for a review. Replay shows that it was missing the stumps and the on-field decision stands. Good start though for the Aussies!
Bowls it short and outside off, Devon Thomas leaves it alone.
Goes fuller this time, Devon Thomas blocks it solidly back towards the bowler.
On a length and on leg, Devon Thomas flicks it towards the leg side. Dot again.
FOUR! Fine shot. A half volley outside off, Devon Thomas gets on his knee and plays a cover drive through covers for a boundary!
Good length outside off shaping it away, Devon Thomas leaves it alone.
On a length angling it in, Jason Holder defends it to short covers.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Jason Holder fends it to the fielder at gully.
Good length from Scott Boland and outside off as Jason Holder shoulders arms at it.
Another length ball and on off, Jason Holder defends it to gully.
Bowls it outside off angling it in a bit, Jason Holder reads it well and makes a tight leave.
Fuller one and on off, Jason Holder knocks it to mid off. Marnus Labuschagne does well to stop it. Scott Boland starts with a maiden.
Fuller and on leg, Devon Thomas defends it back towards the bowler.
Good length and outside off, Devon Thomas defends it with soft hands towards the slips.
Slightly shorter one and on off, Devon Thomas looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Bowls it outside off, Devon Thomas shoulders arms at it.
Another one outside off as Devon Thomas lets this one go as well.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Half of the West Indies squad is back into the hut now. This is on a good length and outsode off, Devon Thomas gets on his knee and looks to drive it but misses and gets the slightest of the edge. Alex Carey behind the stumps makes no mistake and pouches it comfortbly. Mitchell Starc gets an early breakthrough for the Aussies!
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: On a length and on leg, Jason Holder defends it solidly.
Good length and on leg, Jason Holder flicks it to backward square leg for a brace.
Fuller one and on off, Jason Holder defends it to mid off.
On a length angling it into the batter, Jason Holder blocks it to mid on.
Another one angling it in, Jason Holder defends it to mid off.
Slightly shorter one, on middle. Jason Holder fends it to backward square leg for one.
Fuller and outside off, Jason Holder looks to drive it but misses. Close!
On a length and outside off, shaping it in. Jason Holder makes a tight leave.
Another one on a length, Jason Holder defends it to short covers.
On a length and just outside off, Jason Holder looks to defend it but misses. Mitchell Starc is getting closer to his second here!
Bowls it just outside leg, Jason Holder lets it go.
Good length and outside off, Jason Holder shoulders arms at it. A maiden from Mitchell Starc.
On a length and on off, Joshua Da Silva taps it to the fielder at mid off.
Bowls it outside off, Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter one and on leg, Joshua Da Silva looks to defend it but misses and gets a hit on his thigh as the ball bounces off the deck. Dot.
This one lands outside off, Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Joshua Da Silva leaves this alone as well.
FOUR! Bowls it fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva gets on his knee and drives it past covers for a boundary!

OUT! TIMBER! What a beauty from Mitchell Starc. An inswinger and on off, Jason Holder looks to defend it but the late swing from Mitchell Starc beats him on the inside edge. The ball rattles the stumps and Mitchell Starc gets his third wicket of the innings.
Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Fuller one and on off, Roston Chase knocks it to covers for a brace.
Slightly shorter one and on leg, Roston Chase fends it to short mid-wicket.
On a length and outside off, Roston Chase leaves it alone.
Fuller one and on off, Roston Chase flicks it to square leg for one.

FOUR! Lucky one! Fuller and outside off, Joshua Da Silva looks to drive it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball goes through the left of the keeper and races away the fine leg fence for a boundary.
This one lands on off, Roston Chase defends it solidly.
Good length with some extra bounce, Roston Chase defends it to the fielder at gully.
Fuller and on off, Roston Chase taps it to mid off. Dot.
Good length shaping it in, Roston Chase defends it to mid on.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Roston Chase leaves it alone.
Good length and on off, Roston Chase defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Joshua Da Silva fends it to point.
On a length and on off, Joshua Da Silva guides it to deep backward point. The fielder has a long chase to do which he does. They collect two.
Bowls it shorter and outside off, Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone.
Another one outside off as Joshua Da Silva leaves this one as well.
On a length and on off, Joshua Da Silva knocks it to mid off and scampers through for a single.
FOUR! Outside off this time, Roston Chase guides it through third man. Nathan Lyon looked to chase it but couldn't. Boundary! Nathan Lyon comes into the attack now.
Fuller and on leg, Joshua Da Silva flicks it to fine leg.
Another one on leg as this is defended again.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Joshua Da Silva punches it to short covers.
Fuller one this time, Joshua Da Silva tucks it but finds the fielder at square leg.
Bowls it on off, Joshua Da Silva defends it to point.
Bowls it outside off, Joshua Da Silva taps it to the fielder at covers. Michael Neser comes into the attack now.
Goes fuller and on leg, Roston Chase flicks it to square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Joshua Da Silva defends it solidly.
Another one on off, Joshua Da Silva blocks it to the fielder at mid off.
Bowls it on off again, Joshua Da Silva eases it to mid on.
Another dot ball as this is again defended towards the fielder at mid on.
Fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva guides it to the fielder at short covers.
Slightly shorter one, on leg. Roston Chase blocks it to mid on.
Bowls it on off turning it in, Roston Chase looks to block it but gets his thigh. Dot.
Fuller one this time, Roston Chase lunges and defends it away.
Tosses it up on off, Roston Chase guides it to backward point for one.
Fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva covers his line and defends it away.
Another one on off, Joshua Da Silva blocks it to short leg.
Good length and just outside off, Roston Chase looks to defend it but misses.
Another one just outside off, Roston Chase looks to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge. Close!
Fuller one on off, Roston Chase defends it solidly.
Fuller again, on off. Roston Chase eases it to mid on.
FOUR! Slightly shorter one, Roston Chase stands tall and pulls it through backward square leg for a boundary!
On a length and outside off, Roston Chase shoulders arms at it.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Joshua Da Silva defends it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva eases it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one, Joshua Da Silva lunges and defends it away.
Similar to the last delivery as Joshua Da Silva defends this out again.
Nathan Lyon keeps it bowling fuller and on off, Joshua Da Silva blocks it well.
This one lands on leg, Joshua Da Silva looks to pull it but misses and gets his pads. A maiden from Nathan Lyon.
Bangs a shorter one on off, Roston Chase lets it go.
Fuller and on middle, Roston Chase defends it to mid off.
On a length and on off, Roston Chase defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, Roston Chase defends it with soft hands back towards the bowler.
Good length and outside off, Roston Chase looks to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Slightly shorter one and outside off, Roston Chase shoulders arms at it.
On off, defended to mid off.
Slightly shorter one, Joshua Da Silva blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it down leg, Joshua Da Silva flicks it but finds the fielder at square leg.
Tosses it up on middle, Joshua Da Silva covers his line and blocks it out.

Tossed up on middle turning it away, Joshua Da Silva looks to block it but misses and gets his thigh. Travis Head at the leg slips and takes a great catch. Players think it was his bat but Nathan Lyon shakes his head and doesn't opt for a review. Australia are getting closer here!
Fuller one and on middle, Joshua Da Silva lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Michael Neser gets his first wicket and breaks a gritty stand of Chase and Da Silva. The ploy to push Carey close to the stumps has done wonders here for the Aussies. It is a length ball, around off, turning away a touch. Chase stays back and tries to flick it away. Although, all he gets is a thick outside edge. Alex Carey though gets a bit fortunate as the ball hits him on his shoulder, but still not taking away his presence of mind to gather the ball, as he goes down on both knees. It needed something special to break this stand and Carey just provided us with a moment of brilliance.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Michael Neser

Commentary: Bowls it outside off, Alzarri Joseph leaves it alone.
Fuller one and on off, Alzarri Joseph taps it to deep covers for three runs.
FOUR! This is down leg. Joshua Da Silva stays back and clips it down to fine leg for a boundary.
Good length and on leg, Joshua Da Silva defends it solidly.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another blinder fro Alex Carey here. Bowls it on a length and just outside off, Joshua Da Silva looks to play at it but the ball kisses the outside edge of his bat and Alex Carey behing the stumps takes an excellent catch. West Indies are eight down in a jiffy now! Michael Neser gets two wickets in a over.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Michael Neser

Commentary: Tossed up on middle, Alzarri Joseph looks to play at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. A stifled appeal turned down.

OUT! TIMBER! Nathan Lyon gets his first wicket. Australia now only need 1 wicket for a win here. It is tossed up, wide of off. Alzarri Joseph steps down the ground and looks to go big over the bowler, although he gets beaten by the sharp turn as the ball grips and turns in. The ball goes through to rattle the stumps.
Howout: b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Fuller one and on off, Marquino Mindley defends it solidly.
Quicker and on off, Marquino Mindley defends it out.

Dropped! Quicker and on leg turning it in, Marquino Mindley looks to block it but gets the inner part of the bat as the ball goes towards Travis Head at leg slips and he fails to grab on it. A tough chance though.
Fuller and outside off, Marquino Mindley looks to play at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length, on the pads, Anderson Phillip blocks it out.
A length ball, on top of off. Anderson Phillip dead bats it.
Woah! Touch fuller, wide of off. Anderson Phillip looks to leave it alone but is a bit late and gets a nick as he tries to pull his blade out of the way.
A single now as this is driven to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Michael Neser walks back with a three-fer. Incredible performance by the Aussies. It is a length ball, on fourth stump. Marquino Mindley gets a thick outside edge. Alex Carey dives to his right behind the sticks and takes a stunning one-handed catch. Australia win the game by 419 runs.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Michael Neser
